bwaVLUnitHwVersion.name: bwaVLUnitHwVersion
bwaVLUnitHwVersion.description: Applicable to all units. Hardware platform version.

bwaVLRunningSoftwareVersion.name: bwaVLRunningSoftwareVersion
bwaVLRunningSoftwareVersion.description: Applicable to all units. Running software version.

bwaVLRunningFrom.name: bwaVLRunningFrom
bwaVLRunningFrom.description: Applicable to all units. The memory (main or shadow) from which the current version is running from.

bwaVLMainVersionNumber.name: bwaVLMainVersionNumber
bwaVLMainVersionNumber.description: Applicable to all units. Main software version number.

bwaVLMainVersionFileName.name: bwaVLMainVersionFileName
bwaVLMainVersionFileName.description: Applicable to all units. Main software version file name.

bwaVLShadowVersionNumber.name: bwaVLShadowVersionNumber
bwaVLShadowVersionNumber.description: Applicable to all units. Shadow software version number.

bwaVLShadowVersionFileName.name: bwaVLShadowVersionFileName
bwaVLShadowVersionFileName.description: Applicable to all units. Shadow software version file name.

bwaVLUnitMacAddress.name: bwaVLUnitMacAddress
bwaVLUnitMacAddress.description: Applicable to all units. Unit hardware MAC address.

bwaVLUnitType.name: bwaVLUnitType
bwaVLUnitType.description: Applicable to all units. auBS (1) : AU-BS (modular access unit). auSA (2) : AU-SA (stand-alone access unit). su-6-1D (3) : SU-6-1D (subscriber unit supporting 6 Mbps) su-6-BD (4) : SU-6-BD (subscriber unit supporting 6 Mbps). su-24-BD (5) : SU-24-BD (subscriber unit supporting 24 Mbps). bu-B14 (6) : BU-B14 (PtP Base Unit supporting 14 Mbps). bu-B28 (7) : BU-B28 (PtP Base Unit supporting 28 Mbps). rb-B14 (8) : RB-B14 (PtP Remote Bridge supporting 14 Mbps). rb-B28 (9) : RB-B28 (PtP Remote Bridge supporting 28 Mbps). su-BD (10) : SU-BD (subscriber unit). su-54-BD(11) : SU-54-BD (subscriber unit supporting 54 Mbps). su-3-1D (12) : SU-3-1D (subscriber unit supporting 3 Mbps). su-3-4D (13) : SU-3-4D (subscriber unit supporting 3 Mbps). ausBS (14) : AUS-BS (modular access unit supporting maxim 8 or 25 (via licensing) subscribers and allowing association only with SU-3 or SU-6). ausSA (15) : AUS-SA (stand-alone access unit supporting maxim 8 or 25 (via licensing)subscribers and allowing association only with SU-3 or SU-6 ). auBS4900(16) : AU-BS-4900 (BWA 4900 modular access unit) auSA4900(17) : AU-SA-4900 (BWA 4900 stand alone access unit) suBD4900(18) : SU-BD-4900 (BWA 4900 subscriber unit) bu-B100 (19) : BU-B100 (PtP Base Unit unlimited throughput) rb-B100 (20) : BU-B100 (PtP Remote Bridge unlimited throughput) su-I (21) : SU-I au-E (22) : AU-E

bwaVLAssociatedAU.name: bwaVLAssociatedAU
bwaVLAssociatedAU.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Associated AU/BU MAC address.

bwaVLNumOfAssociationsSinceLastReset.name: bwaVLNumOfAssociationsSinceLastReset
bwaVLNumOfAssociationsSinceLastReset.description: Applicable to all units. The number of associations since last reset, including duplicate associations (re-associations).

bwaVLCurrentNumOfAssociations.name: bwaVLCurrentNumOfAssociations
bwaVLCurrentNumOfAssociations.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The number of SUs currently associated with the AU. BWA-PtP products return 65535.

bwaVLUnitBootVersion.name: bwaVLUnitBootVersion
bwaVLUnitBootVersion.description: Applicable to all units. Boot version.

bwaVLRadioBand.name: bwaVLRadioBand
bwaVLRadioBand.description: Applicable to all units. The unit's radio band.

bwaVLCurrentEthernetPortState.name: bwaVLCurrentEthernetPortState
bwaVLCurrentEthernetPortState.description: Applicable to all units. The current Ethernet port state.

bwaVLTimeSinceLastReset.name: bwaVLTimeSinceLastReset
bwaVLTimeSinceLastReset.description: Applicable to all units. The elapsed time since last reset.

bwaVLCountryCode.name: bwaVLCountryCode
bwaVLCountryCode.description: Applicable to all units. The country code and country name or country group name that is supported by the unit.

bwaVLCountryDependentParamsTable.name: bwaVLCountryDependentParamsTable
bwaVLCountryDependentParamsTable.description: Applicable to all units. A table of country dependent parameters.

bwaVLCountryDependentParameterEntry.name: bwaVLCountryDependentParameterEntry
bwaVLCountryDependentParameterEntry.description: Applicable to all units. An entry in the Country Dependent Parameters table.

bwaVLCountryDependentParameterTableIdx.name: bwaVLCountryDependentParameterTableIdx
bwaVLCountryDependentParameterTableIdx.description: Applicable to all units. The sub-band ID of the entry in the Country Dependent Parameters table. Serves also as index for the table entry.

bwaVLCountryDependentParameterFrequencie.name: bwaVLCountryDependentParameterFrequencies
bwaVLCountryDependentParameterFrequencie.description: Applicable to all units. The frequencies included in the applicable sub-band entry.

bwaVLAllowedBandwidth.name: bwaVLAllowedBandwidth
bwaVLAllowedBandwidth.description: Applicable to all units. The bandwidth when using the applicable the sub-band.

bwaVLRegulationMaxTxPowerAtAntennaPort.name: bwaVLRegulationMaxTxPowerAtAntennaPort
bwaVLRegulationMaxTxPowerAtAntennaPort.description: Applicable to all units. The maximum allowed Tx power when using the applicable sub-band. A RegulationMaxTxPowerAtAntennaPort of 255, means no limit

bwaVLRegulationMaxEIRP.name: bwaVLRegulationMaxEIRP
bwaVLRegulationMaxEIRP.description: Applicable to all units. The maximum Tx EIRP when using the applicable sub-band. A Regulation Max EIRP of 0, means no limit.

bwaVLMinModulationLevel.name: bwaVLMinModulationLevel
bwaVLMinModulationLevel.description: Applicable to all units. The minimum supported modulation level.

bwaVLMaxModulationLevel.name: bwaVLMaxModulationLevel
bwaVLMaxModulationLevel.description: Applicable to all units. The maximum supported modulation level.

bwaVLBurstModeSupport.name: bwaVLBurstModeSupport
bwaVLBurstModeSupport.description: Applicable to all units. The supported Burst Mode Option.

bwaVLMaximumBurstDuration.name: bwaVLMaximumBurstDuration
bwaVLMaximumBurstDuration.description: Applicable to all units. Applicable only if Burst Mode Option is supported. The maximum supported burst duration.

bwaVLDfsSupport.name: bwaVLDfsSupport
bwaVLDfsSupport.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The supported Dfs Option.

bwaVLMinimumHwRevision.name: bwaVLMinimumHwRevision
bwaVLMinimumHwRevision.description: Applicable to all units. The Minimum HW Revision needed to support the country code.

bwaVLAuthenticationEncryptionSupport.name: bwaVLAuthenticationEncryptionSupport
bwaVLAuthenticationEncryptionSupport.description: Applicable to all units. The supported Authentication Encryption Option.

bwaVLDataEncryptionSupport.name: bwaVLDataEncryptionSupport
bwaVLDataEncryptionSupport.description: Applicable to all units. The supported Data Encryption Option.

bwaVLAESEncryptionSupport.name: bwaVLAESEncryptionSupport
bwaVLAESEncryptionSupport.description: Applicable to all units. The supported AES Encryption Option.

bwaVLAntennaGainChange.name: bwaVLAntennaGainChange
bwaVLAntennaGainChange.description: Applicable to all units. Indicates whether the Antenna Gain parameter is changeable or fixed.

bwaVLAteTestResults.name: bwaVLAteTestResults
bwaVLAteTestResults.description: Applicable to all units. Results of ATE Test

bwaVLSerialNumber.name: bwaVLSerialNumber
bwaVLSerialNumber.description: Applicable to all units. Serial Number of the unit

bwaVLResetUnit.name: bwaVLResetUnit
bwaVLResetUnit.description: Applicable to all units. Resets the unit and applies new parameter values.

bwaVLSetDefaults.name: bwaVLSetDefaults
bwaVLSetDefaults.description: Applicable to all units. Sets unit configuration to Defaults values after the next reset. noDefaultSettingRequested : Read-Only Option, no Default setting was Issued. completeFactory : All parameters revert to Factory Defaults values. partialFactory : All parameters revert to Factory Defaults values, except the parameters required for maintaining wireless connectivity. completeOperator: All parameters revert to Operator Defaults values. partialOperator : All parameters revert to Operator Defaults values, except the parameters required for maintaining wireless connectivity. cancelCurrentPendingRequest : Default Setting request is cancelled.

bwaVLUnitName.name: bwaVLUnitName
bwaVLUnitName.description: Applicable to all units. The unit name. A string of up to 32 printable ASCII characters.

bwaVLFlashMemoryControl.name: bwaVLFlashMemoryControl
bwaVLFlashMemoryControl.description: Applicable to all units. resetAndBootFromShadowVersion : Activates the backup version. useRunningVersionAfterReset : The currently active version will become the main version and will be activated after next reset.

bwaVLTelnetLogoutTimer.name: bwaVLTelnetLogoutTimer
bwaVLTelnetLogoutTimer.description: Applicable to all units. Time-out of management via Telnet program. Automatic exit if the program is inactive for the defined time. Range: 1 to 999 (minutes).

bwaVLSaveCurrentConfigurationAsOperatorD.name: bwaVLSaveCurrentConfigurationAsOperatorDefaults
bwaVLSaveCurrentConfigurationAsOperatorD.description: Applicable to all units. Saves the current configuration as Operator Defaults. Cannot be executed after requesting set defaults and the unit was not reset.

bwaVLExitTelnet.name: bwaVLExitTelnet
bwaVLExitTelnet.description: Applicable to all units. Exit the management via Telnet program.

bwaVLReadOnlyPassword.name: bwaVLReadOnlyPassword
bwaVLReadOnlyPassword.description: Applicable to all units. The User (read only) password. This is also the Read Community String. Up to 8 printable ASCII characters.

bwaVLInstallerPassword.name: bwaVLInstallerPassword
bwaVLInstallerPassword.description: Applicable to all units. The Installer password. Up to 8 printable ASCII characters.

bwaVLAdminPassword.name: bwaVLAdminPassword
bwaVLAdminPassword.description: Applicable to all units. The Administrator password. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password). Up to 8 printable ASCII characters.

bwaVLEthernetNegotiationMode.name: bwaVLEthernetNegotiationMode
bwaVLEthernetNegotiationMode.description: Applicable to all units. The speed/duplex mode of the Ethernet port.

bwaVLFTPServerUserName.name: bwaVLFTPServerUserName
bwaVLFTPServerUserName.description: Applicable to all units. The user name to be used for access to the FTP server. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password).

bwaVLFTPServerPassword.name: bwaVLFTPServerPassword
bwaVLFTPServerPassword.description: Applicable to all units. The password to be used for access to the FTP server. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password).

bwaVLFTPClientIPAddress.name: bwaVLFTPClientIPAddress
bwaVLFTPClientIPAddress.description: Applicable to all units. For SW version higher than 4.0 this is read-only. The IP address of the FTP stack in the unit.

bwaVLFTPServerIpAddress.name: bwaVLFTPServerIpAddress
bwaVLFTPServerIpAddress.description: Applicable to all units. The IP address of the FTP server.

bwaVLFTPClientMask.name: bwaVLFTPClientMask
bwaVLFTPClientMask.description: Applicable to all units. The Mask of the FTP stack in the unit.

bwaVLFTPGatewayIpAddress.name: bwaVLFTPGatewayIpAddress
bwaVLFTPGatewayIpAddress.description: Applicable to all units. The FTP Gateway address

bwaVLFTPSwFileName.name: bwaVLFTPSwFileName
bwaVLFTPSwFileName.description: Applicable to all units. The name of the SW file to be downloaded.

bwaVLFTPSwSourceDir.name: bwaVLFTPSwSourceDir
bwaVLFTPSwSourceDir.description: Applicable to all units. The source directory of the required file in the FTP server. Up to 80 printable ASCII characters. Use dot (.) To clear field

bwaVLFTPDownloadSwFile.name: bwaVLFTPDownloadSwFile
bwaVLFTPDownloadSwFile.description: Applicable to all units. Execution of the SW download operation

bwaVLConfigurationFileName.name: bwaVLConfigurationFileName
bwaVLConfigurationFileName.description: Applicable to all units. The name of the configuration file to be downloaded/uploaded.

bwaVLOperatorDefaultsFileName.name: bwaVLOperatorDefaultsFileName
bwaVLOperatorDefaultsFileName.description: Applicable to all units. The name of the Operator Defaults file to be downloaded/uploaded

bwaVLFTPConfigurationFileSourceDir.name: bwaVLFTPConfigurationFileSourceDir
bwaVLFTPConfigurationFileSourceDir.description: Applicable to all units. The source directory of the required file in the FTP server. Up to 80 printable ASCII characters. Use dot (.) To clear field

bwaVLExecuteFTPConfigurationFileLoading.name: bwaVLExecuteFTPConfigurationFileLoading
bwaVLExecuteFTPConfigurationFileLoading.description: Applicable to all units. Execution of the file download/upload operation.

bwaVLEventLogFileName.name: bwaVLEventLogFileName
bwaVLEventLogFileName.description: Applicable to all units. The name of the Event Log file to be uploaded.

bwaVLEventLogDestinationDir.name: bwaVLEventLogDestinationDir
bwaVLEventLogDestinationDir.description: Applicable to all units. The destination directory of the event log file. Up to 80 printable ASCII characters. Use dot (.) To clear field.

bwaVLUploadEventLogFile.name: bwaVLUploadEventLogFile
bwaVLUploadEventLogFile.description: Applicable to all units. Execution of the event log upload operation.

bwaVLLoadingStatus.name: bwaVLLoadingStatus
bwaVLLoadingStatus.description: Applicable to all units. The status of the last loading operation.

bwaVLEventLogPolicy.name: bwaVLEventLogPolicy
bwaVLEventLogPolicy.description: Applicable to all units. The lowest level event to be registered in the event log.

bwaVLEraseEventLog.name: bwaVLEraseEventLog
bwaVLEraseEventLog.description: Applicable to all units. Erase the event log.

bwaVLSystemLocation.name: bwaVLSystemLocation
bwaVLSystemLocation.description: Applicable to all units. The unit location.

bwaVLFeatureUpgradeManually.name: bwaVLFeatureUpgradeManually
bwaVLFeatureUpgradeManually.description: Applicable to all units. Upgrade unit to support new feature. Enter your license number (32 to 64 hex digits).

bwaVLChangeUnitType.name: bwaVLChangeUnitType
bwaVLChangeUnitType.description: Applicable RB/BU only. Change the unit type between BU and RB.

bwaLighteAPWorkingMode.name: bwaLighteAPWorkingMode
bwaLighteAPWorkingMode.description: Applicable to AU only. Change unit running mode: 0 - VL mode 1 - Mixed cell mode

bwaVLAccessToNwMng.name: bwaVLAccessToNwMng
bwaVLAccessToNwMng.description: Applicable to all units. The port to be used for remote management.

bwaVLNwMngFilter.name: bwaVLNwMngFilter
bwaVLNwMngFilter.description: Applicable to all units. Disables or enable on one of the ports, or on both ports, IP address based filtering of management messages (e.g. SNMP , Telnet , TFTP , DHCP).

mngIpFilterTable.name: mngIpFilterTable
mngIpFilterTable.description: Applicable to all units. A Management IP Filter Table of up to 3 IP addresses of devices that are authorized to access the unit for management purposes.

mngIpFilterEntry.name: mngIpFilterEntry
mngIpFilterEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A Management IP Filter Table entry.

bwaVLNwMngIpAddress.name: bwaVLNwMngIpAddress
bwaVLNwMngIpAddress.description: Applicable to all units. An IP address in the Management IP Filter Table.

bwaVLNwMngIpTableIdx.name: bwaVLNwMngIpTableIdx
bwaVLNwMngIpTableIdx.description: Applicable to all units. A table index for an entry in the Management IP Filter Table.

bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpAddr.name: bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpAddr
bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpAddr.description: Applicable to all units. 0 - cancel operation. 1..10 - Deletes a single selected entry from the Management IP Filter Table.

bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpAddrs.name: bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpAddrs
bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpAddrs.description: Applicable to all units. Deletes all entries from the Management IP Filter Table.

bwaVLAccessToNwTrap.name: bwaVLAccessToNwTrap
bwaVLAccessToNwTrap.description: Applicable to all units. Enables or disables sending of traps.

mngTrapTable.name: mngTrapTable
mngTrapTable.description: Applicable to all units. A Management Trap Table of up to 10 IP addresses of stations to send traps to.

mngTrapEntry.name: mngTrapEntry
mngTrapEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A Management Trap Table entry.

bwaVLNwMngTrapCommunity.name: bwaVLNwMngTrapCommunity
bwaVLNwMngTrapCommunity.description: Applicable to all units. The trap community associated with the applicable entry in the Management Trap Table. Up to 14 printable case sensitive ASCII characters.

bwaVLNwMngTrapAddress.name: bwaVLNwMngTrapAddress
bwaVLNwMngTrapAddress.description: Applicable to all units. An IP address in the Management Trap Table entry.

bwaVLNwTrapTableIdx.name: bwaVLNwTrapTableIdx
bwaVLNwTrapTableIdx.description: Applicable to all units. Tables Index for an entry in the Management Trap Table.

bwaVLDeleteOneTrapAddr.name: bwaVLDeleteOneTrapAddr
bwaVLDeleteOneTrapAddr.description: Applicable to all units. 0 - cancel operation. 1..10 - Deletes a single selected entry from the Management Trap Table.

bwaVLDeleteAllTrapAddrs.name: bwaVLDeleteAllTrapAddrs
bwaVLDeleteAllTrapAddrs.description: Applicable to all units. Deletes all entries from the Management Trap Table.

bwaVLMngIpRangesTable.name: bwaVLMngIpRangesTable
bwaVLMngIpRangesTable.description: Applicable to all units. Table of Management IP Address Ranges

bwaVLMngIpRangeEntry.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeEntry
bwaVLMngIpRangeEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A Management IP Address Ranges Table entry

bwaVLMngIpRangeIdx.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeIdx
bwaVLMngIpRangeIdx.description: Applicable to all units. Index of an entry in the Management IP Address Ranges Table

bwaVLMngIpRangeFlag.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeFlag
bwaVLMngIpRangeFlag.description: Applicable to all units. Defines the method of defining the range: Using Start & End Address( rangeDefinedByStartEndAddr ), or using Start Address and Mask ( rangeDefinedByStartAddrSubNetMask ).

bwaVLMngIpRangeStart.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeStart
bwaVLMngIpRangeStart.description: Applicable to all units. Start Address of the range

bwaVLMngIpRangeEnd.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeEnd
bwaVLMngIpRangeEnd.description: Applicable to all units. End Address of the range. Used only if bwaVLMngIpRangeFlag is rangeDefinedByStartEndAddr

bwaVLMngIpRangeMask.name: bwaVLMngIpRangeMask
bwaVLMngIpRangeMask.description: Applicable to all units. End Address of the range. Used only if bwaVLMngIpRangeFlag is rangeDefinedByStartAddrMask

bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpRange.name: bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpRange
bwaVLDeleteOneNwIpRange.description: Applicable to all units. 0 - cancel operation. 1..10 - Deletes a single selected entry from the Management IP Ranges Table.

bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpRanges.name: bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpRanges
bwaVLDeleteAllNwIpRanges.description: Applicable to all units. Deletes all entries from the Management IP Ranges Table.

bwaVLApClientIpAddress.name: bwaVLApClientIpAddress
bwaVLApClientIpAddress.description: Applicable to SU/RB unit only. The IP Address of the WIFI WIMAX unit

bwaVLUnitIpAddress.name: bwaVLUnitIpAddress
bwaVLUnitIpAddress.description: Applicable to all units. IP address of the unit.

bwaVLSubNetMask.name: bwaVLSubNetMask
bwaVLSubNetMask.description: Applicable to all units. Subnet mask of the unit.

bwaVLDefaultGWAddress.name: bwaVLDefaultGWAddress
bwaVLDefaultGWAddress.description: Applicable to all units. Default gateway IP address of the unit.

bwaVLUseDhcp.name: bwaVLUseDhcp
bwaVLUseDhcp.description: Applicable to all units. DHCP client mode of operation. disabled : Use regular (manual) methods to configure IP parameters. dHCP Only: Use DHCP server to configure IP parameters. automatic: Use DHCP server to configure IP parameters. If a DHCP server is not available, use manually configured values.

bwaVLAccessToDHCP.name: bwaVLAccessToDHCP
bwaVLAccessToDHCP.description: Applicable to all units. The port to be used for communicating with a DHCP server.

bwaVLRunTimeIPaddr.name: bwaVLRunTimeIPaddr
bwaVLRunTimeIPaddr.description: Applicable to all units. The run-time IP address. If DHCP is used the Run Time IP Address is the address given to the unit by the server. Otherwise it is the manually configured address.

bwaVLRunTimeSubNetMask.name: bwaVLRunTimeSubNetMask
bwaVLRunTimeSubNetMask.description: Applicable to all units. The run-time Subnet Mask. If DHCP is used the Run Time Subnet Mask is the mask given to the unit by the server. Otherwise it is the manually configured mask.

bwaVLRunTimeDefaultIPGateway.name: bwaVLRunTimeDefaultIPGateway
bwaVLRunTimeDefaultIPGateway.description: Applicable to all units. The run-time Gateway IP address. If DHCP is used the Run Time Gateway IP Address is the address given to the unit by the server. Otherwise it is the manually configured address.

bwaVLVlanID.name: bwaVLVlanID
bwaVLVlanID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. VLAN ID for data frame tagging. Applicable to Access Link only. Range: 1 to 4094. 0 - not applicable.

bwaVLEthernetLinkType.name: bwaVLEthernetLinkType
bwaVLEthernetLinkType.description: Applicable to all units. VLAN support mode (Link Type). The Access Link option is not available for AU/BU. Service Provider Link is not available for BU/RB.

bwaVLManagementVlanID.name: bwaVLManagementVlanID
bwaVLManagementVlanID.description: Applicable to all units. VLAN ID for management frame tagging. Range: 1 to 4094, 65535 for No VLAN tagging.

bwaVLVlanForwardingSupport.name: bwaVLVlanForwardingSupport
bwaVLVlanForwardingSupport.description: Applicable to all units. Enables or disables the VLAN forwarding feature. (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanForwardingTable.name: bwaVLVlanForwardingTable
bwaVLVlanForwardingTable.description: Applicable to all units. A VLAN Forwarding Table of up to 20 VLAN IDs of devices to which data frames are forwarded when VLAN Forwarding is Enabled. (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanForwardingEntry.name: bwaVLVlanForwardingEntry
bwaVLVlanForwardingEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A VLAN Forwarding Table entry. (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanForwardingTableIdx.name: bwaVLVlanForwardingTableIdx
bwaVLVlanForwardingTableIdx.description: Applicable to all units. A read only table index for a VLAN entry in the VLAN Forwarding Table.

bwaVLVlanIdForwarding.name: bwaVLVlanIdForwarding
bwaVLVlanIdForwarding.description: Applicable to all units. The list of VLAN ID's in the VLAN ID Forwarding Table. To Remove a VLAN ID - SET the corresponding entry to 0. To Add a new VLAN ID SET an entry which is currently 0. Range : 0 to 4094

bwaVLVlanRelayingSupport.name: bwaVLVlanRelayingSupport
bwaVLVlanRelayingSupport.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Enables or disables VLAN Relaying (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanRelayingTable.name: bwaVLVlanRelayingTable
bwaVLVlanRelayingTable.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. A VLAN Relaying Table of up to 20 VLAN IDs of devices to which data frames are relayed when VLAN Relaying is Enabled. (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanRelayingEntry.name: bwaVLVlanRelayingEntry
bwaVLVlanRelayingEntry.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. A VLAN Relaying Table entry. (applicable in Trunk and Service Provider links only).

bwaVLVlanRelayingTableIdx.name: bwaVLVlanRelayingTableIdx
bwaVLVlanRelayingTableIdx.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. A table index for a VLAN entry in the VLAN Relaying Table.

bwaVLVlanIdRelaying.name: bwaVLVlanIdRelaying
bwaVLVlanIdRelaying.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The list of VLAN ID's in the VLAN ID Relaying Table. To Remove a VLAN ID - SET the corresponding entry to 0. To Add a new VLAN ID SET an entry which is currently 0. Range: 0 to 4094 , 0 - remove entry.

bwaVLVlanDataPriority.name: bwaVLVlanDataPriority
bwaVLVlanDataPriority.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Priority tagging for data frames. Applicable to Access Link only. Range: 0 to 7.

bwaVLVlanManagementPriority.name: bwaVLVlanManagementPriority
bwaVLVlanManagementPriority.description: Applicable to all units. Priority tagging for management frames. Applicable to Access Link and Trunk Link only. Range: 0 to 7.

bwaVLVlanPriorityThreshold.name: bwaVLVlanPriorityThreshold
bwaVLVlanPriorityThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable to units with SW version 3.1 or higher. Priority threshold for tagged frames received from Ethernet port. Applicable to Hybrid Link and Trunk Link only. Valid values: 0-7.

bwaVLQinQEthertype.name: bwaVLQinQEthertype
bwaVLQinQEthertype.description: Applicable to AU and SU. Not applicable to PtP units. The Ethernet type of the Service Provider Tag. The range is 0x8101(33025) - 0x9000(36864), 0x9100(37120), 0x9200(37376).

bwaVLQinQProviderVlanID.name: bwaVLQinQProviderVlanID
bwaVLQinQProviderVlanID.description: Applicable to SU only. VLAN ID of the Service Provider Tag.

bwaVLBridgeAgingTime.name: bwaVLBridgeAgingTime
bwaVLBridgeAgingTime.description: Applicable to all units. Bridge aging time for devices on both the Ethernet and wireless link sides. Range: 20 to 2000 seconds.

bwaVLBroadcastRelaying.name: bwaVLBroadcastRelaying
bwaVLBroadcastRelaying.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Enables/disables the relaying of broadcast messages to the wireless link.

bwaVLUnicastRelaying.name: bwaVLUnicastRelaying
bwaVLUnicastRelaying.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Enables/disables the relaying of unicast messages to the wireless link.

bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering
bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enables/disables the filtering of Ethernet (layer2) broadcasts. disable : No filtering. onEthernetOnly : Filters broadcasts received on the Ethernet port only. onWirelessOnly : Filters broadcasts received on the Wlan port only. onBothWirelessAndEth: Filters broadcasts received on both ports.

bwaVLDHCPBroadcastOverrideFilter.name: bwaVLDHCPBroadcastOverrideFilter
bwaVLDHCPBroadcastOverrideFilter.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enables or disables the broadcasting of DHCP messages, overriding the general *bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering Ethernet broadcast filtering option.

bwaVLPPPoEBroadcastOverrideFilter.name: bwaVLPPPoEBroadcastOverrideFilter
bwaVLPPPoEBroadcastOverrideFilter.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enables or disables the broadcasting of PPPoE messages, overriding the general *bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering Ethernet broadcast filtering option.

bwaVLARPBroadcastOverrideFilter.name: bwaVLARPBroadcastOverrideFilter
bwaVLARPBroadcastOverrideFilter.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enables or disables the broadcasting of ARP messages, overriding the general *bwaVLEthBroadcastFiltering Ethernet broadcast filtering option.

bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterOption.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterOption
bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterOption.description: Applicable to all units. Enable/disable the limiter for multicast and broadcast packets.

bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterThresho.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterThreshold
bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterThresho.description: Applicable to all units. The limit on the number of multicast and broadcast packets when the Ethernet Broadcast/Multicast Limiter Option is enabled. Range: 0 to 204800

bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterSendTra.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterSendTrapInterval
bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticastLimiterSendTra.description: Applicable to all units. The minimum time between two successive traps that are sent indicating the number of packets that were dropped by the Ethernet Broadcast/Multicast Limiter since the last trap was sent. Range: 1 to 60 minutes

bwaVLToSPrecedenceThreshold.name: bwaVLToSPrecedenceThreshold
bwaVLToSPrecedenceThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable to units with SW version 3.1 or higher. Priority threshold (based on the ToS) for frames received from the Ethernet port. Range: 0 to 7.

bwaVLRoamingOption.name: bwaVLRoamingOption
bwaVLRoamingOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Disable/enable the roaming feature. When enabled, the SU/RB will start scanning for an AU/BU after about one second of not receiving beacons or data from current AU/BU. Once it found a new AU/BU, it will also send through the wireless network a roaming SNAP on behalf of its clients informing other devices in the network of their new location. When disabled, it will wait for about seven seconds before starting scanning, and it will not send a roaming SNAP.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTable.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTable
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTable.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. A list of up to 100 MAC Addresses of SUs. If bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAction is set to denyList, these are SUs that are not allowed to transfer data to the AU. If bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAction is set to allowList, only these SUs are allowed to transfer data to the AU.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListEntry.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListEntry
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListEntry.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. An entry in the Mac Address Deny List Table.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTableIdx.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTableIdx
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListTableIdx.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. A read only table index for a MAC Address entry in the Mac Address Deny List Table. Range: 1 to 100.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListId.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListId
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListId.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. The list of MAC Addresses in the Mac Address Deny List Table. To Remove a MAC Address - SET the corresponding entry to 0. To Add a new MAC Address - SET an entry which is currently 0.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAdd.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAdd
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAdd.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. Add a MAC address to the MAC Address Deny List Table

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListRemove.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListRemove
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListRemove.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. Delete a MAC address from the MAC Address Deny List Table

bwaVLNumberOfMacAddressesInDenyList.name: bwaVLNumberOfMacAddressesInDenyList
bwaVLNumberOfMacAddressesInDenyList.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. Number of MAC addresses in the MAC Address Deny List Table.

bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAction.name: bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAction
bwaVLMacAddressDenyListAction.description: Applicable to AU only. Define the action to be used by the Mac Address Deny List. allowedList(2) means that the list becomes Allow list.

bwaVLEthernetPortControl.name: bwaVLEthernetPortControl
bwaVLEthernetPortControl.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enable/disable the Ethernet port. When disabled, only data frames are blocked. Management frames are accepted.

bwaVLESSID.name: bwaVLESSID
bwaVLESSID.description: Applicable to all units. The Extended Service Set ID (ESSID) used to prevent the merging of collocated systems. The ESSID is accessible only with the write community string (administrator password). Up to 31 printable case sensitive ASCII characters.

bwaVLOperatorESSIDOption.name: bwaVLOperatorESSIDOption
bwaVLOperatorESSIDOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Enabling/disabling the use of the Operator ESSID.

bwaVLOperatorESSID.name: bwaVLOperatorESSID
bwaVLOperatorESSID.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. A secondary ESSID to support easy installation of SUs as well as the use of the Best AU/BU feature. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community Up to 31 printable case sensitive ASCII characters.

bwaVLRunTimeESSID.name: bwaVLRunTimeESSID
bwaVLRunTimeESSID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The ESSID of the associated AU/BU. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community. Up to 31 printable ASCII characters, case sensitive.

bwaVLMaximumCellRadius.name: bwaVLMaximumCellRadius
bwaVLMaximumCellRadius.description: Applicable to all units. For AU/BU: read-write. In units with SW version 2.0 and up - applicable only when the Cell Distance Mode is set to Manual. The highest distance from the AU/BU of any SU/RB served by it. Affects the maximum time the units wait for a response message and the slot size by taking into account the round trip propagation delay. For SU/RB: read-only. The distance is learned from the AU/BU. Range: For units below version 2.0 the range is 0 - 50000 Meters. Otherwise - the range is 0 to 54 Kilometers. 0 means no compensation (minimum slot size, maximal delay timeout).

bwaVLAIFS.name: bwaVLAIFS
bwaVLAIFS.description: Applicable to AU and SU. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Not applicable if Wireless Link Prioritization is enabled. Arbitration Inter-Frame Spacing (AIFS) value, in slots. This is the number of time slots that define the DIFS. (DIFS=SIFS+AIFS). A value of 1 should be used only in point-to-point applications to allow one unit to have advantage over the other unit.

bwaVLWirelessTrapThreshold.name: bwaVLWirelessTrapThreshold
bwaVLWirelessTrapThreshold.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. A wireless link quality threshold, expressed in % of retransmissions, for sending the bwaVLAUWirelessQualityTRAP. This trap indicate whether the quality has gone below or above the specified threshold. The Threshold Range: 1 to 100 (% retransmissions).

bwaVLTransmitPowerTable.name: bwaVLTransmitPowerTable
bwaVLTransmitPowerTable.description: Applicable to all units. A table of transmit power parameters.

bwaVLTransmitPowerEntry.name: bwaVLTransmitPowerEntry
bwaVLTransmitPowerEntry.description: Applicable to all units. An entry in the Transmit Power Table.

bwaVLTransmitPowerIdx.name: bwaVLTransmitPowerIdx
bwaVLTransmitPowerIdx.description: Applicable to all units. An index of an entry in the Transmit Power Table.

bwaVLApplicableModulationLevel.name: bwaVLApplicableModulationLevel
bwaVLApplicableModulationLevel.description: Applicable to all units. The applicable modulation level for an entry in the Transmit Power Table. Level 8 is not applicable to units with HW revision A.

bwaVLMaximumTxPowerRange.name: bwaVLMaximumTxPowerRange
bwaVLMaximumTxPowerRange.description: Applicable to all units. The allowed range for the bwaVLTxPower parameter at the applicable modulation level . Range: -10 to the maximum allowed power level at the applicable modulation level , in dBm.

bwaVLTxPower.name: bwaVLTxPower
bwaVLTxPower.description: Applicable to all units. Read-only for units with SW version 4.0 and higher. In AU/BU: The transmit power in dBm defined for the applicable rate. In SU/RB: If ATPC is disabled, this is the transmit power in dBm defined for the applicable rate. If ATPC is enabled, it serves as the initial transmit power in dBm for the ATPC algorithm. In SU/RB: The range is -10 dBm to the power value defined by bwaVLMaximumTxPower for the applicable modulation level. In AU/BU: The range is -10 dBm to the power value defined by bwaVLMaximumTxPowerRange for the applicable modulation level.

bwaVLCurrentTxPower.name: bwaVLCurrentTxPower
bwaVLCurrentTxPower.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The actual transmit power in dBm for the applicable rate. Range: -17 to the maximum value defined by bwaVLMaximumTxPowerRange for the applicable modulation level.

bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerTable.name: bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerTable
bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. A table of maximum transmit power parameters.

bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerEntry.name: bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerEntry
bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An entry in the Maximum Transmit Power Table.

bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerIdx.name: bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerIdx
bwaVLMaximumTransmitPowerIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An index of an entry in the Maximum Transmit Power Table.

bwaVLMaxTxApplicableModulationLevel.name: bwaVLMaxTxApplicableModulationLevel
bwaVLMaxTxApplicableModulationLevel.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The applicable modulation level for an entry in the Maximum Transmit Power Table. Level 8 is not applicable to units with HW revision A.

bwaVLDefinedMaximumTxPowerRange.name: bwaVLDefinedMaximumTxPowerRange
bwaVLDefinedMaximumTxPowerRange.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The allowed range for the bwaVLMaxTxPower parameter at the applicable modulation level . Range: -10 to the maximum allowed power level at the applicable modulation level , in dBm.

bwaVLMaxTxPower.name: bwaVLMaxTxPower
bwaVLMaxTxPower.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Read-only for units with SW version 4.0 and higher. The maximum value that can be configured for the bwaVLTxPower parameter. This is also the maximum power level that can be reached by the ATPC algorithm. The range is -10 dBm to the maximum value defined by bwaVLDefinedMaximumTxPowerRange for the applicable modulation level.

bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociations.name: bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociations
bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociations.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Sets the upper limit for the number of SUs that can be associated with the AU. Range: For regular AUs (AU-BS, AU-SA) the range is from 0 to 512 if encryption is disabled the range id form 0 to 124 if encryption is enabled For AUS-BS and AUS-SA with SW version 4.0 and higher the range is between 0 to 8 or 25 (via licensing). For AUS-BS and AUS-SA with SW version below 4.0 the range is between 0 to 5. BWA-PtP products return 65535.

bwaVLBestAuSupport.name: bwaVLBestAuSupport
bwaVLBestAuSupport.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Disable/enable the Best AU/BU selection mechanism.

bwaVLBestAuNoOfScanningAttempts.name: bwaVLBestAuNoOfScanningAttempts
bwaVLBestAuNoOfScanningAttempts.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The number of scanning attempts to collect information for the Best AU/BU decision. Range: 1 to 255.

bwaVLPreferredAuMacAddress.name: bwaVLPreferredAuMacAddress
bwaVLPreferredAuMacAddress.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The MAC address of the preferred AU/BU (overriding the Best AU/BU selection process). 000000000000 means no preferred AU/BU.

bwaVLNeighborAuTable.name: bwaVLNeighborAuTable
bwaVLNeighborAuTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. A table of data on neighboring AUs/BUs.

bwaVLNeighborAuEntry.name: bwaVLNeighborAuEntry
bwaVLNeighborAuEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An entry in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuIdx.name: bwaVLNeighborAuIdx
bwaVLNeighborAuIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An index of an entry in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuMacAdd.name: bwaVLNeighborAuMacAdd
bwaVLNeighborAuMacAdd.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. A MAC address of an AU/BU in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuESSID.name: bwaVLNeighborAuESSID
bwaVLNeighborAuESSID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The ESSID of an AU/BU in the Neighbor AU/BU Table. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community.

bwaVLNeighborAuSNR.name: bwaVLNeighborAuSNR
bwaVLNeighborAuSNR.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The received signal quality (SNR) in dB of an AU/BU in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuAssocLoadStatus.name: bwaVLNeighborAuAssocLoadStatus
bwaVLNeighborAuAssocLoadStatus.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU association load status in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuMark.name: bwaVLNeighborAuMark
bwaVLNeighborAuMark.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU mark in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuHwRevision.name: bwaVLNeighborAuHwRevision
bwaVLNeighborAuHwRevision.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU HW revision in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuCountryCode.name: bwaVLNeighborAuCountryCode
bwaVLNeighborAuCountryCode.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU supported country code in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuSwVer.name: bwaVLNeighborAuSwVer
bwaVLNeighborAuSwVer.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU SW version in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuAtpcOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuAtpcOption
bwaVLNeighborAuAtpcOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU ATPC option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuAdapModOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuAdapModOption
bwaVLNeighborAuAdapModOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU adaptive modulation option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuBurstModeOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuBurstModeOption
bwaVLNeighborAuBurstModeOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU burst mode option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuDfsOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuDfsOption
bwaVLNeighborAuDfsOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU DFS option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuConcatenationOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuConcatenationOption
bwaVLNeighborAuConcatenationOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU concatenation option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuLearnCountryCodeBySU.name: bwaVLNeighborAuLearnCountryCodeBySU
bwaVLNeighborAuLearnCountryCodeBySU.description: Applicable to SU only. Starting with 4.0 is not applicable for BWA 4900 and BWA PtP products. Neighbor AU Learn Country Code by SU configuration in the Neighbor AU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuSecurityMode.name: bwaVLNeighborAuSecurityMode
bwaVLNeighborAuSecurityMode.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU security mode configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuAuthOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuAuthOption
bwaVLNeighborAuAuthOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU authentication option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuDataEncyptOption.name: bwaVLNeighborAuDataEncyptOption
bwaVLNeighborAuDataEncyptOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Neighbor AU/BU data encryption option configuration in the Neighbor AU/BU Table.

bwaVLNeighborAuPerSuDistanceLearning.name: bwaVLNeighborAuPerSuDistanceLearning
bwaVLNeighborAuPerSuDistanceLearning.description: Applicable to SU only. Neighbor AU per SU distance learning option configuration in the Neighbor AU Table.

bwaVLSubBandLowerFrequency.name: bwaVLSubBandLowerFrequency
bwaVLSubBandLowerFrequency.description: Applicable to SU only. Not applicable to units with SW version 2.0 or higher. The lowest frequency in the subset to be used for scanning. For 5.8GHz products the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For 4.9GHz products the range is 4920 to 5080 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For HW Revision C and above this leaf is not relevant - shall return 0.

bwaVLSubBandUpperFrequency.name: bwaVLSubBandUpperFrequency
bwaVLSubBandUpperFrequency.description: Applicable to SU only. Not applicable to units with SW version 2.0 or higher. The highest frequency in the subset to be used for scanning. For 5.8GHz products the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For 4.9GHz products the range is 4920 to 5080 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For HW Revision C and above this leaf is not relevant - shall return 0.

bwaVLScanningStep.name: bwaVLScanningStep
bwaVLScanningStep.description: Applicable to all units - For flexible Sub-Bands only. For units with version 2.0 and above this is a read-only parameter. The scanning step to be used for generating the frequency subset.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetTable.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetTable
bwaVLFrequencySubsetTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The Frequency Subset Table that includes all frequencies from the selected Sub-band.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetEntry.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetEntry
bwaVLFrequencySubsetEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. An entry in the Frequency Subset Table.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetTableIdx.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetTableIdx
bwaVLFrequencySubsetTableIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. An index of an entry in the Frequency subset Table.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequency.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequency
bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequency.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. Applicable to all units with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). The frequency in MHz of an entry in the Frequency Subset table.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetActive.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetActive
bwaVLFrequencySubsetActive.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The status of an entry in the Frequency subset Table. The frequency of an active entry will be included in the final list of frequencies to be used for scanning.

bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew.name: bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew
bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The frequency in MHz of an entry in the Frequency Subset table. (Replaces bwaVLFrequencySubsetFrequency to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher).

bwaVLSetSelectedFreqSubset.name: bwaVLSetSelectedFreqSubset
bwaVLSetSelectedFreqSubset.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. Apply the selected subset. After the next reset the new subset will be used.

bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTable.name: bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTable
bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The Current Frequency Subset table. In SU/RB it includes all frequencies that are currently used for scanning. In AU/BU it includes all frequencies that can be used by the DFS mechanism (if applicable)

bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetEntry.name: bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetEntry
bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. An entry in the Current Frequency Subset Table.

bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTableIdx.name: bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTableIdx
bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetTableIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB and to AU/BU. An index of an entry in the Current Frequency subset Table. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher.

bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequency.name: bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequency
bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequency.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. Applicable to all units with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). The frequency in MHz of an entry in the Current Frequency Subset table.

bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew.name: bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew
bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequencyNew.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The frequency in MHz of an entry in the Current Frequency Subset table. (Replaces bwaVLCurrentFrequencySubsetFrequency to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher).

bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequency.name: bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequency
bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequency.description: Applicable to AU/BU with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLCurrentUOperatingFrequencyNew to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). The operating frequency in MHz. For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For units with SW version 2.0 and up the range is as defined in the selected Sub Band.

bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequencyNew.name: bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequencyNew
bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequencyNew.description: Applicable to AU/BU. The operating frequency in MHz. (Replaces bwaVLCurrentAUOperatingFrequency to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher). For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For units with SW version 2.0 and up the range is as defined in the selected Sub Band.

bwaVLAUDefinedFrequency.name: bwaVLAUDefinedFrequency
bwaVLAUDefinedFrequency.description: Applicable to AU/BU with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLAUDefinedFrequencyNew to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 this is the frequency in MHz of the AU/BU after the next reset. For units with SW version 2.0 and up this is the frequency in MHz to use when the DFS Option is disabled. For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For units with SW version 2.0 and up the range is as defined in the selected Sub Band.

bwaVLAUDefinedFrequencyNew.name: bwaVLAUDefinedFrequencyNew
bwaVLAUDefinedFrequencyNew.description: Applicable to AU/BU. For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 this is the frequency in MHz of the AU/BU after the next reset. For units with SW version 2.0 and up this is the frequency in MHz to use when the DFS Option is disabled. (Replaces bwaVLAUDefinedFrequency to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher). For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For units with SW version 2.0 and up the range is as defined in the selected Sub Band.

bwaVLCurrentSUOperatingFrequency.name: bwaVLCurrentSUOperatingFrequency
bwaVLCurrentSUOperatingFrequency.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The frequency used currently by the unit. For 5.8GHz products with SW version below 2.0 the range is 5740 to 5830 MHz using 10MHz resolution. For units with SW version 2.0 and up the range is as defined in the selected Sub Band.

bwaVLSelectSubBandIndex.name: bwaVLSelectSubBandIndex
bwaVLSelectSubBandIndex.description: Applicable to all units with SW version below 4.0 For units with SW version 4.0 and up it is applicable only for AU/BU. For SU/RB it defines only the sub-band for the Spectrum Analyzer. The ID of the sub-band used by the unit.

bwaVLDFSOption.name: bwaVLDFSOption
bwaVLDFSOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Enabling/disabling the DFS Algorithm. Not applicable if DFS Option is not supported by the current Sub Band.

bwaVLDFSChannelCheckTime.name: bwaVLDFSChannelCheckTime
bwaVLDFSChannelCheckTime.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Defines the time the unit checks the channel for presence of radar signals and does not transmit after power up or association or after moving to a new channel due to detecting radar in the used channel. Range: 1 to 3600 (seconds).

bwaVLDFSChannelAvoidancePeriod.name: bwaVLDFSChannelAvoidancePeriod
bwaVLDFSChannelAvoidancePeriod.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Defines the time after detecting radar signals in a channel of avoiding using the channel or adjacent channels in accordance with the bandwidth. Range: 1 to 60 (minutes).

bwaVLDFSSuWaitingOption.name: bwaVLDFSSuWaitingOption
bwaVLDFSSuWaitingOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Defines whether the associated SUs should wait for this AU/BU after it stopped transmitting due to radar detection, before they starts scanning for other AUs/BUs.

bwaVLDFSClearRadarDetectedChannelsAfterR.name: bwaVLDFSClearRadarDetectedChannelsAfterReset
bwaVLDFSClearRadarDetectedChannelsAfterR.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Clear Radar Detected and Adjacent to Radar channels after unit reset. Returns the unit to operate in default frequency.

bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsTable.name: bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsTable
bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsTable.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Applicable only when DFS option is on. Displays the current channels defined in the sub-band and their radar detection status.

bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsEntry.name: bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsEntry
bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsEntry.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. An entry in the bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsTable.

bwaVLDFSChannelIdx.name: bwaVLDFSChannelIdx
bwaVLDFSChannelIdx.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Read-only. The index of the entry in the bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelsTable.

bwaVLDFSChannelFrequency.name: bwaVLDFSChannelFrequency
bwaVLDFSChannelFrequency.description: Applicable to AU/BU with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLDFSChannelFrequency New to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). The frequency in MHz of a channel in the DFS Radar Detection Channels Table.

bwaVLDFSChannelRadarStatus.name: bwaVLDFSChannelRadarStatus
bwaVLDFSChannelRadarStatus.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The radar detection status of a channel in bwaVLDFSRadarDetectionChannelTable.

bwaVLDFSChannelFrequencyNew.name: bwaVLDFSChannelFrequencyNew
bwaVLDFSChannelFrequencyNew.description: Applicable to AU/BU. The frequency of a channel in the DFS Radar Detection Channels Table. (Replaces bwaVLDFSChannelFrequency to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher).

bwaVLDFSMinimumPulsesToDetect.name: bwaVLDFSMinimumPulsesToDetect
bwaVLDFSMinimumPulsesToDetect.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Defines the minimum number of pulses to detect a radar. Range: 1 - 100.

bwaVLDFSChannelReuseOption.name: bwaVLDFSChannelReuseOption
bwaVLDFSChannelReuseOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Enabling/disabling the DFS Channel Reuse Algorithm. Not applicable if DFS Option is not supported by the current Sub Band.

bwaVLDFSRadarActivityAssessmentPeriod.name: bwaVLDFSRadarActivityAssessmentPeriod
bwaVLDFSRadarActivityAssessmentPeriod.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Range: 1 to 12 (Houres).

bwaVLDFSMaximumNumberOfDetectionsInAsses.name: bwaVLDFSMaximumNumberOfDetectionsInAssessmentPeriod
bwaVLDFSMaximumNumberOfDetectionsInAsses.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Range: 1 to 10 (Times).

bwaVLCountryCodeLearningBySU.name: bwaVLCountryCodeLearningBySU
bwaVLCountryCodeLearningBySU.description: Applicable to AU only. Starting with 4.0 it is nor applicable for BWA 4900 and BWA PtP. Defines whether the SUs learn the country code of the AU.

bwaVLAutoSubBandSelectedFreqSubset.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandSelectedFreqSubset
bwaVLAutoSubBandSelectedFreqSubset.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. Apply the selected subset. After the next reset the new subset will be used for scanning.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetTable.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetTable
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The Frequency Subset Table that includes all available sub-bands and all the frequencies in these sub-bands.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetEntry.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetEntry
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. An entry in the Frequency Subset Table.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetBandIdx.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetBandIdx
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetBandIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The index of the applicable Sub Band. This is the Sub Band ID of the relevant entry in the Country Dependent Parameters table. Serves also as an index of the entry in the Frequency subset Table.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequency.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequencyIdx
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequency.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The index of the applicable frequency in the applicable Sub Band. Serves also as an index of the entry in the Frequency subset Table.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetActive.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetActive
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetActive.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The status of an entry in the Auto Sub Band Frequency subset Table. The frequency of an active entry will be included in the final list of frequencies to be used for scanning.

bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequency.name: bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequency
bwaVLAutoSubBandFrequencySubsetFrequency.description: Applicable to SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The frequency in MHz of the entry in the Auto Sub Band Frequency Subset table.

bwaVLAtpcOption.name: bwaVLAtpcOption
bwaVLAtpcOption.description: Applicable all units. Enabling/disabling the ATPC Algorithm.

bwaVLDeltaFromMinSNRLevel.name: bwaVLDeltaFromMinSNRLevel
bwaVLDeltaFromMinSNRLevel.description: Applicable AU/BU only. The Minimum SNR Level plus the value of this parameter define the maximum desired level of the average SNR at the AU/BU. If the ATPC Option is enabled, than if the received SNR is above the maximum desired level, the AU/BU will transmit Power-Down messages to the applicable SU/RB. Range: 4 to 20 (dB).

bwaVLMinimumSNRLevel.name: bwaVLMinimumSNRLevel
bwaVLMinimumSNRLevel.description: Applicable AU/BU only. Defines the minimum desired level of the average SNR at the AU/BU. Below this level, if *AtpcOption is enabled, the AU/BU will transmit ATPC Power-Up messages to the applicable SU/RB. The *MinimumSNRLevel cannot be higher than *MaximumSNRLevel. Range: 4 to 60 (dB).

bwaVLMinimumIntervalBetweenATPCMessages.name: bwaVLMinimumIntervalBetweenATPCMessages
bwaVLMinimumIntervalBetweenATPCMessages.description: Applicable AU/BU only. The minimum interval between two consecutive AU/BU to SU/RB messages. Range: 1 to 3600 (Sec).

bwaVLPowerLevelSteps.name: bwaVLPowerLevelSteps
bwaVLPowerLevelSteps.description: Applicable AU/BU only. The step in dB that the SU/RB will use when receiving an ATPC Power-Up/Power-Down message. Range: 1 to 20 (dB).

bwaVLCellDistanceMode.name: bwaVLCellDistanceMode
bwaVLCellDistanceMode.description: Applicable AU/BU only. The selected mode of deciding on Cell Distance.

bwaVLFairnessFactor.name: bwaVLFairnessFactor
bwaVLFairnessFactor.description: Applicable AU/BU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products for SW version below 4.0.. The percentage of the maximum distance that is taken into account in the time slot calculation. Range: 0 to 100 (Percent). A value of 0 means the minimal slot size (9 microseconds). BWA-PtP products with SW version below 4.0 return na.

bwaVLMeasuredCellDistance.name: bwaVLMeasuredCellDistance
bwaVLMeasuredCellDistance.description: Applicable AU/BU only. The Maximum Cell Distance as calculated by the AU/BU. Range: 0 to 54 (Kilometers).

bwaVLUnitWithMaxDistance.name: bwaVLUnitWithMaxDistance
bwaVLUnitWithMaxDistance.description: Applicable AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP units. The MAC address of the unit with the maximum distance from the AU.

bwaVLPerSuDistanceLearning.name: bwaVLPerSuDistanceLearning
bwaVLPerSuDistanceLearning.description: Aplicable to AU only. Applicable only if Cell Distance Mode is set to Automatic. When disabled, all SUs in the cell will use for the ACK Timeout the computed distance of the farthest SU. When enabled, each SU will use its own computed distance

bwaVLScanningMode.name: bwaVLScanningMode
bwaVLScanningMode.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The scanning mode. In cells where the DFS Option is enabled Scanning Mode is forced to Passive.

bwaVLAntennaGain.name: bwaVLAntennaGain
bwaVLAntennaGain.description: Applicable to all units. Read-write in units where bwaVLAntennaGainChange is supported. Read-only in units where bwaVLAntennaGainChange is not supported. The net gain (including cable attenuation for detached antennas) of the antenna. Range: 0 - to Maximum EIRP defined by country code + 10 (dBi). A value of -2 (this value is configurable only in factory) means don't care. A value of -1 (this value is configurable only in factory) means that the unit will not transmit until the actual value is configured.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisChannelScanPeriod.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisChannelScanPeriod
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisChannelScanPeriod.description: Applicable to all units. The period of staying on each channel for information gathering when performing Spectrum analysis. Range: 2-30 seconds.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisScanCycles.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisScanCycles
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisScanCycles.description: Applicable to all units. The number of scanning cycles when performing Spectrum Analysis. Range: 1-100.

bwaVLAutomaticChannelSelection.name: bwaVLAutomaticChannelSelection
bwaVLAutomaticChannelSelection.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Defines weather the AU/BU shall choose the most noise free channel upon startup after spectrum analysis.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisActivation.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisActivation
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisActivation.description: Applicable to all units. Activates spectrum analysis, the unit is automatically reset upon activation.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisStatus.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisStatus
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisStatus.description: Applicable to all units. Defines weather the unit is currently under performing a spectrum analysis process.

bwaVLResetSpectrumCounters.name: bwaVLResetSpectrumCounters
bwaVLResetSpectrumCounters.description: Applicable to all units. Resets the spectrum analysis counters.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTable.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTable
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTable.description: Applicable to all units. The spectrum analysis information table.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationEntry.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationEntry
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationEntry.description: Applicable to all units. The spectrum analysis information table entry.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTableIdx.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTableIdx
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationTableIdx.description: Applicable to all units. A read only table index for a Spectrum Analysis Information entry in the Spectrum Analysis Information Table.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationChannel.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationChannel
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationChannel.description: Applicable to all units. The channels in the Spectrum Analysis Information Table. If the unit is currently under spectrum analysis the channels would be those on which the analysis is currently performed. If the unit is in normal mode the channels would be the those on which the last analysis was performed.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalCo.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalCount
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalCo.description: Applicable to all units. The number of signals (excluding OFDM frames) detected in the channel. If the unit is currently under spectrum analysis the count would be of the analysis that is currently performed. If the unit is in normal mode the count would be of the last analysis performed.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalSN.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalSNR
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalSN.description: Applicable to all units. The approximate SNR of the signals (excluding OFDM frames) detected in the channel. If the unit is currently under spectrum analysis the SNR would be of the analysis that is currently performed. If the unit is in normal mode the SNR would be of the last analysis performed.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalWi.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalWidth
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationSignalWi.description: Applicable to all units. The average width of the signals (excluding OFDM frames) detected in the channel. If the unit is currently under spectrum analysis the width would be of the analysis that is currently performed. If the unit is in normal mode the width would be of the last analysis performed.

bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationOFDMFram.name: bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationOFDMFrames
bwaVLSpectrumAnalysisInformationOFDMFram.description: Applicable to all units. The number of OFDM frames detected in the channel. If the unit is currently under spectrum analysis the count would be of the analysis that is currently performed. If the unit is in normal mode the count would be of the last analysis performed.

bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociationsLimit.name: bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociationsLimit
bwaVLMaxNumOfAssociationsLimit.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Shows the limit for the number of SUs that can be associated with the AU. For AU-BS, AU-SA if Data Encryption is enabled, the upper limit is 124, otherwise it is 512. For AUS-BS, AUS-SA with SW version 4.0 and higher the upper limit is 8 or 25 (via licensing). For AUS-BS, AUS-SA with SW version below 4.0 the upper limit is 5. BWA-PtP products return 65535.

bwaVLDisassociateAllSUs.name: bwaVLDisassociateAllSUs
bwaVLDisassociateAllSUs.description: Applicable to AU only. The AU shall disassociate all its associated units.

bwaVLDisassociateSuByMacAddress.name: bwaVLDisassociateSuByMacAddress
bwaVLDisassociateSuByMacAddress.description: Applicable to AU only. The AU shall disassociate the SU with the configured MAC address.

bwaVLTxControl.name: bwaVLTxControl
bwaVLTxControl.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Tx Control of the AU/BU. Starting with version 4.0 it is run-time. For SW version below 4.0 the unit reset itself. If set to ethernetStatusControl, the unit will not transmit if the Ethernet link is down. This parameter can be configured only via the ethernet port.

bwaVLLostBeaconsWatchdogThreshold.name: bwaVLLostBeaconsWatchdogThreshold
bwaVLLostBeaconsWatchdogThreshold.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The number of unsuccessful consecutive transmissions beacons before Internal refresh is performed. 0 means that the lost beacons watchdog is not used and internal refresh is not performed.

bwaVLTransmitPower.name: bwaVLTransmitPower
bwaVLTransmitPower.description: Applicable to all units with SW version 4.0 and higher. The uniform transmit power for all modulation levels. For a specific modulation level the effective transmit power (bwaVLTxPower) is the minimum between the uniform transmit power and the maximum transmit power for that modulation level.

bwaVLMaximumTxPower.name: bwaVLMaximumTxPower
bwaVLMaximumTxPower.description: Applicable to only SU/RB with SW version 4.0 and higher. The Maximum Transmit Power for all modulation levels. The Maximum Transmit Power for a specific modulation level is the minimum between this parameter and the hardware limitation for that modulation level

bwaLCountryCodeReApply.name: bwaLCountryCodeReApply
bwaLCountryCodeReApply.description: Applicable to all units. Re-apply country code parameters.

bwaVLMirDownlink.name: bwaVLMirDownlink
bwaVLMirDownlink.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The Maximum Information Rate (MIR) from AU/BU to SU/RB. MIR must be above bwaVLCirDownlink value. Range for set: 128 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-3 with SW version below 4.0, 128 to 3,072 (Kbps) for SU-3 with SW version 4.0 and higher, 128 to 3,968 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version less than 4.0, 128 to 6,016 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version greater than 4.0, 128 to 14,976 (Kbps) for SU-24, 128 to 53,888 (Kbps) for SU-BD and SU-54, 128 to 6,912 (Kbps) for RB-14, 128 to 22,016 (Kbps) for RB-28, 128 to 107,904 (Kbps) for RB-100. 128 to 6,016 (Kbps) for SU-I. The actual value (Get) will be the entered value rounded to the nearest multiple of 128 (N*128).

bwaVLMirUplink.name: bwaVLMirUplink
bwaVLMirUplink.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The Maximum Information Rate (MIR) from SU/RB to AU/BU. MIR must be above bwaVLCirUplink value. Range for set: 128 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-3, 128 to 3,968 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version less than 4.0, 128 to 4,096 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version greater than 4.0, 128 to 14,976 (Kbps) for SU-24, 128 to 53,888 (Kbps) for SU-BD and SU-54, 128 to 6,912 (Kbps) for RB-14, 128 to 22,016 (Kbps) for RB-28, 128 to 107,904 (Kbps) for RB-100. 128 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-I. The actual value (Get) will be the entered value rounded to the nearest multiple of 128 (N*128).

bwaVLCirDownlink.name: bwaVLCirDownlink
bwaVLCirDownlink.description: Applicable to SU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The Committed Information Rate (CIR) from AU to SU. CIR must be below bwaVLMirDownlink value. Range for Set: 0 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-3 with SW version below 4.0, 0 to 3,072 (Kbps) for SU-3 with SW version 4.0 and higher, 0 to 3,968 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version less than 4.0, 0 to 6,016 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version greater than 4.0 0 to 14,976 (Kbps) for SU-24, 0 to 45,056 (Kbps) for SU-BD and SU-54. 0 to 6,016 (Kbps) for SU-I. The actual value (Get) will be the entered value rounded to the nearest multiple of 128 (N*128). BWA-PtP products will return 65535.

bwaVLCirUplink.name: bwaVLCirUplink
bwaVLCirUplink.description: Applicable to SU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The Committed Information Rate (CIR) from SU to AU. CIR must be below bwaVLMirUplink value. Range for Set: 0 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-3, 0 to 3,968 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version less than 4.0, 0 to 4,096 (Kbps) for SU-6 with SW version greater than 4.0, 0 to 14,976 (Kbps) for SU-24, 0 to 45,056 (Kbps) for SU-BD and SU-54. 0 to 2,048 (Kbps) for SU-I. The actual value (Get) will be the entered value rounded to the nearest multiple of 128 (N*128). BWA-PtP products will return 65535.

bwaVLMaxDelay.name: bwaVLMaxDelay
bwaVLMaxDelay.description: Applicable to SU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The maximal time packets may be delayed by the CIR\MIR mechanism. Above the configured maximal period the packets are discarded. Range: 300 to 10000 milliseconds. BWA-PtP products return 65535.

bwaVLMaxBurstDuration.name: bwaVLMaxBurstDuration
bwaVLMaxBurstDuration.description: Applicable to AU and SU. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The maximum time during which inactivity bonus time can be accumulated for future burst transmissions. Range: 0 to 2000 milliseconds. BWA-PtP products return 65535

bwaVLGracefulDegradationLimit.name: bwaVLGracefulDegradationLimit
bwaVLGracefulDegradationLimit.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The maximum limit for activating the graceful degradation algorithm. Range: 0 to 70% rate of the CIR. BWA-PtP products return 255.

bwaVLMirOnlyOption.name: bwaVLMirOnlyOption
bwaVLMirOnlyOption.description: Applicable to AU only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. When bwaMirOnly is enabled, it overrides the CIR/MIR algorithm for determining actual information rate and forces the algorithm to operate with MIR parameter settings only. When enabled, the Graceful Degradation algorithm is disabled.

bwaVLVLANPriorityThreshold.name: bwaVLVLANPriorityThreshold
bwaVLVLANPriorityThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. If the VLAN Priority's value of the frame is less than or equal to this threshold the frame will get LOW priority, otherwise the frame will get HIGH priority. Untagged frames will get LOW priority

bwaVLToSPrioritizationOption.name: bwaVLToSPrioritizationOption
bwaVLToSPrioritizationOption.description: Applicable to all units. Disable/Enable IP ToS prioritization and choose the interpretation of the IP ToS field from IP header. ipPrecedence(2): The IP ToS field is defined by RFC791. In this case the prioritization will be done using the Precedence sub-field of IP ToS. This sub-field has 3 bits, so it can be between 0 and 7. dSCP(3): The IP ToS field is defined by RFC2474. In this case the prioritization will be done using the DSCP sub-field. The size of the sub-field is 6 bits, so the range is 0 to 63.

bwaVLIPPrecedenceThreshold.name: bwaVLIPPrecedenceThreshold
bwaVLIPPrecedenceThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. The threshold of Precedence sub-field of IP ToS field from IP Header (RFC791) to be used when the ToS Prioritization Option is set to IP Precedence. If the Precedence sub-field of a frame is less than or equal to this threshold the frame will have LOW priority, otherwise it will get HIGH priority.

bwaVLIPDSCPThreshold.name: bwaVLIPDSCPThreshold
bwaVLIPDSCPThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. The threshold of DSCP sub-field of IP ToS field from IP Header (RFC2474) to be used when ToS Prioritization Option is set to DSCP. If the DSCP sub-field of a frame is less than or equal to this threshold the frame will have LOW priority, otherwise it will get HIGH priority.

bwaVLUdpTcpPortRangePrioritizationOption.name: bwaVLUdpTcpPortRangePrioritizationOption
bwaVLUdpTcpPortRangePrioritizationOption.description: Applicable to all units. Disable/Enable Prioritization using UDP and/or TCP Port Ranges. udpOnly(2) : prioritization will be done only for UDP packets tcpOnly(3) : prioritization will be done only for TCP packets udpANDtcp(4): prioritization will be done for UDP and TCP packets

bwaVLUdpPortPriRTPRTCP.name: bwaVLUdpPortPriRTPRTCP
bwaVLUdpPortPriRTPRTCP.description: Applicale to all units. RTP/RTCP ports prioritization option for UDP packets. rtpANDrtcp(1): the possible RTP and RTCP packet with destination port in the defined port ranges will get HIGH priority rtpOnly(2): only possible RTP packet (packet with even destination port ) with destination port in the defined port ranges will get HIGH priority.

bwaVLUdpPortRangeNum.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeNum
bwaVLUdpPortRangeNum.description: Applicable to all units. The number of entries in the UDP Port Range Table

bwaVLUdpPortRangeTable.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeTable
bwaVLUdpPortRangeTable.description: Applicable to all units. A table of UDP port ranges use for prioritization. The user can define up to 64 ranges. An entry is empty if start is 65535 and end is 0

bwaVLUdpPortRangeEntry.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeEntry
bwaVLUdpPortRangeEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A UDP Port Ranges Table entry.

bwaVLUdpPortRangeStart.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeStart
bwaVLUdpPortRangeStart.description: Applicable to all units. Start port of an UDP Port Range

bwaVLUdpPortRangeEnd.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeEnd
bwaVLUdpPortRangeEnd.description: Applicable to all units. End port of an UDP Port Range

bwaVLUdpPortRangeIdx.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeIdx
bwaVLUdpPortRangeIdx.description: Applicable to all units. UDP Port Range Entry's index

bwaVLUdpPortRangeAdd.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeAdd
bwaVLUdpPortRangeAdd.description: Applicable to all units. Add port range(s) to UDP Port Ranges Table. Get operation will return the empty string. A range is defined <start>-<end> or <start> where <start> is the Start Port of the range and <end> is the End Port. If only <start> is specified the range is <start>-<start>. The value of <start> and <end> are between 0..65535. The user can add several ranges using a comma to separate between ranges. Example: 10-256,99,987-900

bwaVLUdpPortRangeDelete.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeDelete
bwaVLUdpPortRangeDelete.description: Applicable to all units. Delete port range(s) from UDP Port Ranges Table. Get operation will return the empty string. A range is defined <start>-<end> or <start> where <start> is the Start Port of the range and <end> is the End Port. If only <start> is specified the range is <start>-<start>. The value of <start> and <end> are between 0..65535. The user can delete several ranges using a comma to separate between ranges. Example: 10-256,99,987-900

bwaVLUdpPortRangeDeleteAll.name: bwaVLUdpPortRangeDeleteAll
bwaVLUdpPortRangeDeleteAll.description: Applicable to all units. Delete all entries form UDP Port Ranges Table. Get operation will return 1

bwaVLTcpPortPriRTPRTCP.name: bwaVLTcpPortPriRTPRTCP
bwaVLTcpPortPriRTPRTCP.description: Applicable to all units. RTP/RTCP ports prioritization option for TCP packets. rtpANDrtcp(1): the possible RTP and RTCP packet with destination port in the defined port ranges will get HIGH priority rtpOnly(2): only possible RTP packet (packet with even destination port )

bwaVLTcpPortRangeNum.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeNum
bwaVLTcpPortRangeNum.description: Applicable to all units. The number of entries in the TCP Port Range Table

bwaVLTcpPortRangeTable.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeTable
bwaVLTcpPortRangeTable.description: Table of TCP Port Ranges use for prioritization. The user can define up to 64 ranges. An entry is empty if start is 65535 and end is 0

bwaVLTcpPortRangeEntry.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeEntry
bwaVLTcpPortRangeEntry.description: Applicable to all units. A TCP Port Ranges Table entry.

bwaVLTcpPortRangeStart.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeStart
bwaVLTcpPortRangeStart.description: Applicable to all units. Start port of a TCP Port Range

bwaVLTcpPortRangeEnd.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeEnd
bwaVLTcpPortRangeEnd.description: Applicable to all units. End port of a TCP Port Range

bwaVLTcpPortRangeIdx.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeIdx
bwaVLTcpPortRangeIdx.description: Applicable to all units. TCP Port Range Entry's index

bwaVLTcpPortRangeAdd.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeAdd
bwaVLTcpPortRangeAdd.description: Applicable to all units. Add port range(s) to TCP Port Ranges Table. Get operation will return the empty string. A range is defined <start>-<end> or <start> where <start> is the Start Port of the range and <end> is the End Port. If only <start> is specified the range is <start>-<start>. The value of <start> and <end> are between 0..65535. The user can add several ranges using comma to separate between ranges. Example: 10-256,99,987-900

bwaVLTcpPortRangeDelete.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeDelete
bwaVLTcpPortRangeDelete.description: Applicable to all units. Delete port range(s) from TCP Port Ranges Table. Get operation will return the empty string. A range is defined <start>-<end> or <start> where <start> is the Start Port of the range and <end> is the End Port. If only <start> is specified the range is <start>-<start>. The value of <start> and <end> are between 0..65535. The user can delete several ranges using comma to separate between ranges. Example: 10-256,99,987-900

bwaVLTcpPortRangeDeleteAll.name: bwaVLTcpPortRangeDeleteAll
bwaVLTcpPortRangeDeleteAll.description: Applicable to all units. Delete all entries form TCP Port Ranges Table Get operation will return 1

bwaVLWirelessLinkPrioritizationOption.name: bwaVLWirelessLinkPrioritizationOption
bwaVLWirelessLinkPrioritizationOption.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Enable/disable the traffic prioritization over the Wireless Link

bwaVLlowPriorityAIFS.name: bwaVLlowPriorityAIFS
bwaVLlowPriorityAIFS.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Define the AIFS (Arbitration Inter-frame Space) that will be used for transmitting Low Priority Traffic

bwaVLHWRetriesHighPriority.name: bwaVLHWRetriesHighPriority
bwaVLHWRetriesHighPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum number of HW Retries for a unicast data packet that has High Priority

bwaVLHWRetriesLowPriority.name: bwaVLHWRetriesLowPriority
bwaVLHWRetriesLowPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum number of HW Retries for a unicast data packet that has Low Priority
