bwaVLAUBurstDurationHighPriority.name: bwaVLAUBurstDurationHighPriority
bwaVLAUBurstDurationHighPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum duration of burst that can be done by AU with High Priority packets. The time is given in 250 microseconds units

bwaVLAUBurstDurationLowPriority.name: bwaVLAUBurstDurationLowPriority
bwaVLAUBurstDurationLowPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum duration of burst that can be done by AU with Low Priority packets. The time is given in 250 microseconds units

bwaVLSUBurstDurationHighPriority.name: bwaVLSUBurstDurationHighPriority
bwaVLSUBurstDurationHighPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum duration of burst that can be done by SU/RB with High Priority packets. The parameter is configurable in AU and the SUs/RB will learn it form AU/BU. The time is given in 250 microseconds units

bwaVLSUBurstDurationLowPriority.name: bwaVLSUBurstDurationLowPriority
bwaVLSUBurstDurationLowPriority.description: Applicable only to AU with a license for the Wireless Link Prioritization feature and to BU-100. Applicable only if the Wireless Link Prioritization Option is enabled. Defines the Maximum duration of burst that can be done by SU/RB with High Priority packets. The parameter is configurable in AU/BU and the SUs/RB will learn it from AU/BU. The time is given in 250 microseconds units

bwaVLDrapSupport.name: bwaVLDrapSupport
bwaVLDrapSupport.description: Applicable to AU. Not applicable to BWA PtP products. Disable/Enable the DRAP feature

bwaVLDrapUdpPort.name: bwaVLDrapUdpPort
bwaVLDrapUdpPort.description: Applicable to AU when DRAP support is enabled. Not applicable to BWA PtP products. The UDP port used for the DRAP server

bwaVLDrapMaxNumberOfVoiceCalls.name: bwaVLDrapMaxNumberOfVoiceCalls
bwaVLDrapMaxNumberOfVoiceCalls.description: Applicable to AU when DRAP support is enabled. Not applicable to BWA PtP products. The maximum number of voice calls that can be supported by the AU

bwaVLDrapTTL.name: bwaVLDrapTTL
bwaVLDrapTTL.description: Applicable to AU when DRAP support is enabled. Not applicable to BWA PtP products. The maximum time between two allocation requests

bwaVLDrapNoOfActiveVoiceCalls.name: bwaVLDrapNoOfActiveVoiceCalls
bwaVLDrapNoOfActiveVoiceCalls.description: Applicable to AU when DRAP support is enabled. Not applicable to BWA PtP products. The current total number of active voice calls.

bwaVLLowPriorityTrafficMinimumPercent.name: bwaVLLowPriorityTrafficMinimumPercent
bwaVLLowPriorityTrafficMinimumPercent.description: The minimum percent of the traffic rate that is allocated to the low priority traffic

bwaVLSUPMirDownlink.name: bwaVLSUPMirDownlink
bwaVLSUPMirDownlink.description: Applicable to AU only. The Maximum Information Rate (MIR) from AU to SUP. Range for set: 128 to 12,032 (Kbps). The actual value (Get) will be the entered value rounded to the nearest multiple of 128 (N*128).

bwaVLMIRThresholdPercent.name: bwaVLMIRThresholdPercent
bwaVLMIRThresholdPercent.description: Applicable to AU only. MIR Threshold Percent

bwaVLUserFilterOption.name: bwaVLUserFilterOption
bwaVLUserFilterOption.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Defines user-filtering options. disable: No filtering. iPOnly: Only IP protocol frames pass. userDefinedAddrOnly: Only ip frames to/from user defined IP addresses pass. pPPoE Only: Only PPPoE frames pass.

bwaVLIpFilterTable.name: bwaVLIpFilterTable
bwaVLIpFilterTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An IP Filter Table of up to 8 user defined addresses, or address groups, to be used if the selected User Filtering option is userDefinedAddrOnly.

bwaVLIpFilterEntry.name: bwaVLIpFilterEntry
bwaVLIpFilterEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An IP Filter Table entry.

bwaVLIpID.name: bwaVLIpID
bwaVLIpID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An IP address of an IP Filter Table entry.

bwaVLMaskID.name: bwaVLMaskID
bwaVLMaskID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An IP Mask of an IP Filter Table entry. Either a mask or a range, but not both can be used to define an address group. If the range is other than 0, than the mask is ignored and only the range value is used to define the address group.

bwaVLIpFilterRange.name: bwaVLIpFilterRange
bwaVLIpFilterRange.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. An addresses range for the IP Filter Table entry. The first address in the range is the IP address. O means that the range is not used. Either a mask or a range, but not both can be used to define an address group. If the range is other than 0, than the mask is ignored and only the range value is used to define the address group. Range: 0 to 255.

bwaVLIpFilterIdx.name: bwaVLIpFilterIdx
bwaVLIpFilterIdx.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. A table index for the IP Filter Table entry.

bwaVLDeleteOneUserFilter.name: bwaVLDeleteOneUserFilter
bwaVLDeleteOneUserFilter.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Deletes a single selected entry from the IP Filter Table.

bwaVLDeleteAllUserFilters.name: bwaVLDeleteAllUserFilters
bwaVLDeleteAllUserFilters.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Deletes all entries from the IP Filter Table.

bwaVLDHCPUnicastOverrideFilter.name: bwaVLDHCPUnicastOverrideFilter
bwaVLDHCPUnicastOverrideFilter.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. Enables or disables the unicast DHCP messages, overriding the IP Filtering option.

bwaVLAuthenticationAlgorithm.name: bwaVLAuthenticationAlgorithm
bwaVLAuthenticationAlgorithm.description: Applicable to all units. Enables/disables the authentication encryption option. openSystem: Authentication messages are not encrypted. sharedKey : Authentication messages are encrypted

bwaVLSUDefaultKeyID.name: bwaVLSUDefaultKeyID
bwaVLSUDefaultKeyID.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The key to be used for encryption of authentication messages and/or data. Range: 1 to 4.

bwaVLDataEncryptionOption.name: bwaVLDataEncryptionOption
bwaVLDataEncryptionOption.description: Applicable to all units. Enables/disables the data encryption option.

bwaVLAUDefaultMulticastKeyID.name: bwaVLAUDefaultMulticastKeyID
bwaVLAUDefaultMulticastKeyID.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The key to be used for encryption of multicasts and broadcasts.

bwaVLSecurityMode.name: bwaVLSecurityMode
bwaVLSecurityMode.description: Applicable to all units. The fips197 option is applicable only to units with a license to use FIPS 197 algorithm. The encryption algorithm to be used for authentication messages and/or data encryption.

bwaVLAuthenticationPromiscuousMode.name: bwaVLAuthenticationPromiscuousMode
bwaVLAuthenticationPromiscuousMode.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Enables/disable the promiscuous mode allowing authentication of and communication with all SUs/RB regardless of their security parameters.

bwaVLKey1.name: bwaVLKey1
bwaVLKey1.description: Applicable to all units. Key number 1. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password). Valid values: 32 hexadecimal digits.

bwaVLKey2.name: bwaVLKey2
bwaVLKey2.description: Applicable to all units. Key number 2. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password). Valid values: 32 hexadecimal digits.

bwaVLKey3.name: bwaVLKey3
bwaVLKey3.description: Applicable to all units. Key number 3. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password). Valid values: 32 hexadecimal digits.

bwaVLKey4.name: bwaVLKey4
bwaVLKey4.description: Applicable to all units. Key number 4. Accessible only with SNMP Write Community String (administrator password). Valid values: 32 hexadecimal digits.

bwaVLSecurityModeSupport.name: bwaVLSecurityModeSupport
bwaVLSecurityModeSupport.description: Applicable to all units. Returns types of encryption that are supported. 0 - no encryption 1 - WEP 2 - AES OCB 3 - WEP and AES OCB 4 - FIPS-197 5 - FIPS-197 and WEP 6 - FIPS-197 and AES OCB 7 - FIPS-197, AES OCB and WEP

bwaVLRTSThreshold.name: bwaVLRTSThreshold
bwaVLRTSThreshold.description: Applicable to SU and AU. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The minimum frame size that requires an RTS/CTS handshake. Range: For units bearing SW version 3.0 and above: 20 to 3400 bytes, for previous SW versions 20 to 1600 bytes. BWA-PtP products return 65535.

bwaVLMinContentionWindow.name: bwaVLMinContentionWindow
bwaVLMinContentionWindow.description: Applicable to SU and AU. For units bearing SW version 4.0 and above applicable to BWA PtP products, for previous SW versions not applicable to BWA PtP products. The initial value to be used by the contention window calculation algorithm. Value must be 0 or power of 2 minus 1 (7,15,31...). Range: 0 to 1023, excluding 1 and 3. BWA-PtP products with SW version below 4.0 return 65535.

bwaVLMaxContentionWindow.name: bwaVLMaxContentionWindow
bwaVLMaxContentionWindow.description: Applicable to SU and AU. For units bearing SW version 4.0 and above applicable to BWA PtP products, for previous SW versions not applicable to BWA PtP products. The maximum value to be used by the contention window calculation algorithm. Value must be power of 2 minus 1 (7,15,31...) Range: 7 to 1023.

bwaVLMaximumModulationLevel.name: bwaVLMaximumModulationLevel
bwaVLMaximumModulationLevel.description: Applicable to all units. If the Adaptive Modulation algorithm is enabled, it sets the Maximum Modulation Level to be used. If The Modulation algorithm is disabled, it sets the Fixed Modulation Level to be used. The range is 1 to 8. 8 is not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLMulticastModulationLevel.name: bwaVLMulticastModulationLevel
bwaVLMulticastModulationLevel.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The modulation level for multicast and broadcast data frames. The range is 1 to 8. 8 is not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLAvgSNRMemoryFactor.name: bwaVLAvgSNRMemoryFactor
bwaVLAvgSNRMemoryFactor.description: Applicable to all units. The weight of history in average SNR calculation. The higher is the value, the higher is the weight of history. Range: -1 (Disregard History) to 32.

bwaVLHardwareRetries.name: bwaVLHardwareRetries
bwaVLHardwareRetries.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable if Wireless Link Prioritization is enabled. The maximum number of trials to transmit an unacknowledged frame in each Hardware Retrial phase. Range : 1 to 14.

bwaVLAdaptiveModulationAlgorithmOption.name: bwaVLAdaptiveModulationAlgorithmOption
bwaVLAdaptiveModulationAlgorithmOption.description: Applicable to all units. Enables/disables the adaptive modulation level decision mechanism.

bwaVLSoftwareRetrySupport.name: bwaVLSoftwareRetrySupport
bwaVLSoftwareRetrySupport.description: Applicable to all units. Read-only for units with version 2.0. Not applicable for units with SW version 3.0 and higher. The status of the Software Retry mechanism. Enabled when the Adaptive Modulation algorithm is enabled and the Burst Mode Option is disabled. Otherwise it is disabled.

bwaVLNumOfSoftwareRetries.name: bwaVLNumOfSoftwareRetries
bwaVLNumOfSoftwareRetries.description: Applicable to all units. Read-only for units with version 2.0. Not applicable for units with SW version 3.0 and higher. The maximum number of times to use the Software Retry mechanism when it is enabled.

bwaVLMinIntervalBetweenAdaptiveModulatio.name: bwaVLMinIntervalBetweenAdaptiveModulationAlgorithmMessages
bwaVLMinIntervalBetweenAdaptiveModulatio.description: Applicable all units. The minimum interval between two consecutive AU/BU to SU/RB messages. Range: 1 to 3600 (Sec).

bwaVLAdaptiveModulationDecisionThreshold.name: bwaVLAdaptiveModulationDecisionThresholds
bwaVLAdaptiveModulationDecisionThreshold.description: Applicable to all units. Defines the setting of thresholds for the rate decision algorithm. high (2) should typically be used when the SNR is lower than 13dB.

bwaVLBurstModeOption.name: bwaVLBurstModeOption
bwaVLBurstModeOption.description: Applicable to all units. Applicable only if Burst Mode Option is supported by country specific parameters of the Sub Band. Not applicable if Wireless Link Prioritization is enabled. Enables/disable burst mode operation. In SU/RB with HW Revision B or lower blocked(3) value is returned when Security Mode is Wep , Data Encryption Option is Enabled and Burst option is Enabled. In AU/BU with HW Revision B or lower blocked(3) value is returned when Dfs Option is Enabled and Burst mode is enabled.

bwaVLBurstInterval.name: bwaVLBurstInterval
bwaVLBurstInterval.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable if Wireless Link Prioritization is enabled. Burst mode interval in milliseconds. Range: 1 to the maximum value as defined in the country specific parameters of the Sub Band (milliseconds).

bwaVLConcatenationOption.name: bwaVLConcatenationOption
bwaVLConcatenationOption.description: Applicable to all units. Defines the Concatenation option.

bwaVLConcatenationMaximumNumberOfFrames.name: bwaVLConcatenationMaximumNumberOfFrames
bwaVLConcatenationMaximumNumberOfFrames.description: Applicable to all units with SW version 3.X . Not applicable for version 4.0 and higher. Defines the maximum numbers of frames that can be concatenated. Range:2 to 8 (frames).

bwaVLConcatenationMaxFrameSize.name: bwaVLConcatenationMaxFrameSize
bwaVLConcatenationMaxFrameSize.description: Applicable to all units. Defines the maximum size of a concatenated frame. Range: 256 to 2200 (bytes) for BWA PtP products BU/RB14 BU/RB28, or for AU/SU with HW revision A or B. 256 to 4032 (bytes) for AU/SU with HW Revision C or higher and BWA PtP products BU/RB100.

bwaVLAverageReceiveSNR.name: bwaVLAverageReceiveSNR
bwaVLAverageReceiveSNR.description: Applicable to SU/RB only. The average Signal to Noise Ratio of received frames.

bwaVLResetTrafficCounters.name: bwaVLResetTrafficCounters
bwaVLResetTrafficCounters.description: Applicable to all units. Resets the traffic counters.

bwaVLResetPerModulationLevelCounters.name: bwaVLResetPerModulationLevelCounters
bwaVLResetPerModulationLevelCounters.description: Applicable to all units. Resets the per-Modulation Level counters .

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTable.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTable
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTable.description: Applicable to SU/RB. Per Rate Counters table.

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersEntry.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersEntry
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersEntry.description: Applicable to SU/RB. An entry in the Per modulation Counters table.

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTableId.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTableIdx
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTableId.description: Applicable to SU/RB. An index of an entry in the Per modulation level Counters table.

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersApplica.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersApplicableModLevel
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersApplica.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The applicable modulation level of the entry in the Per modulation level Counters table. Modulation Level 8 is not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxSucce.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxSuccess
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxSucce.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The total number of successfully transmitted unicasts at the applicable modulation level.

bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxFaile.name: bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxFailed
bwaVLSUPerModulationLevelCountersTxFaile.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The total number of dropped frames at the applicable Modulation Level.

bwaVLAverageModulationLevel.name: bwaVLAverageModulationLevel
bwaVLAverageModulationLevel.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The average modulation level for successful transmission (rounded to nearest integer) since last reset of the Per Modulation Level counters. Range: 1 to 8.

bwaVLTotalRxFramesViaEthernet.name: bwaVLTotalRxFramesViaEthernet
bwaVLTotalRxFramesViaEthernet.description: Applicable to all units. Total number of frames received via the Ethernet port.

bwaVLTxWirelessToEthernet.name: bwaVLTxWirelessToEthernet
bwaVLTxWirelessToEthernet.description: Applicable to all units. Total number of frames transmitted to the Ethernet port.

bwaVLAUBeaconsToWireless.name: bwaVLAUBeaconsToWireless
bwaVLAUBeaconsToWireless.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The number of beacons transmitted to the wireless media.

bwaVLDataAndOtherMngFramesToWireless.name: bwaVLDataAndOtherMngFramesToWireless
bwaVLDataAndOtherMngFramesToWireless.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The number of data and management frames transmitted to the wireless media. The count includes one count for each data frame transmitted successfully (excluding retransmissions).

bwaVLTotalTxFramesToWireless.name: bwaVLTotalTxFramesToWireless
bwaVLTotalTxFramesToWireless.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames transmitted to the wireless media. The count includes one count for each data frame that was transmitted successfully (excluding retransmissions), and also the number of transmitted control and management frames, including beacons.

bwaVLTotalTransmittedUnicasts.name: bwaVLTotalTransmittedUnicasts
bwaVLTotalTransmittedUnicasts.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The total number of unicast frames successfully transmitted to the wireless media, excluding retransmissions.

bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesD.name: bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesDouble
bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesD.description: Applicable to all products. The total number of double concatenated frames successfully transmitted to the wireless media, excluding retransmissions.

bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesS.name: bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesSingle
bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesS.description: Applicable to all products. The total number of double concatenated frames successfully transmitted to the wireless media, excluding retransmissions.

bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesM.name: bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesMore
bwaVLTotalTransmittedConcatenatedFramesM.description: Applicable to all products. The total number of concatenated frames with more then two frames successfully transmitted to the wireless media, excluding retransmissions.

bwaVLTotalRxFramesFromWireless.name: bwaVLTotalRxFramesFromWireless
bwaVLTotalRxFramesFromWireless.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of frames that were received from the wireless media. The count includes data and control and management frames, including beacons received from the AU/BU. The count does not include frames that were discarded internally, bad frames and duplicate frames.

bwaVLTotalRetransmittedFrames.name: bwaVLTotalRetransmittedFrames
bwaVLTotalRetransmittedFrames.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of retransmissions of data frames (counts all unsuccessful transmissions/retransmissions).

bwaVLFramesDropped.name: bwaVLFramesDropped
bwaVLFramesDropped.description: Applicable to all units. The number of dropped frames. The frames that were retransmitted to the extent of the maximum allowed number of retransmissions without being acknowledged..

bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaHighQueue.name: bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaHighQueue
bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaHighQueue.description: Applicable to all units. Frames submitted to the internal bridge via the High priority queue. for transmission to the wireless media.

bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaMidQueue.name: bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaMidQueue
bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaMidQueue.description: Applicable to all units. Frames submitted to the internal bridge via the Mid priority queue for transmission to the wireless media.

bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaLowQueue.name: bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaLowQueue
bwaVLFramesSubmittedViaLowQueue.description: Applicable to all units. Frames submitted to the internal bridge via the Low priority queue for transmission to the wireless media.

bwaVLTotalNoOfDataFramesSubmitted.name: bwaVLTotalNoOfDataFramesSubmitted
bwaVLTotalNoOfDataFramesSubmitted.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of data frames submitted to the internal bridge for transmission to the wireless media.

bwaVLTotalRecievedDataFrames.name: bwaVLTotalRecievedDataFrames
bwaVLTotalRecievedDataFrames.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of data frames received from the wireless media, including duplicate frames.

bwaVLRecievedBadFrames.name: bwaVLRecievedBadFrames
bwaVLRecievedBadFrames.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames received from the wireless media with errors (CRC errors).

bwaVLNoOfDuplicateFramesDiscarded.name: bwaVLNoOfDuplicateFramesDiscarded
bwaVLNoOfDuplicateFramesDiscarded.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames discarded due to receiving multiple copies.

bwaVLNoOfInternallyDiscardedMirCir.name: bwaVLNoOfInternallyDiscardedMirCir
bwaVLNoOfInternallyDiscardedMirCir.description: Applicable to all units. The number of data frames received from the Ethernet port that were discarded by the MIR/CIR mechanism either to avoid exceeding the maximum allowed information rate, or when the wireless link conditions do not enable reaching the allowed rate.

bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesDouble.name: bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesDouble
bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesDouble.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of double concatenated frames received from the wireless media, including duplicate frames.

bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesSingle.name: bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesSingle
bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesSingle.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of data fast frames single concatenated frames received from the wireless media, including duplicate frames.

bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesMore.name: bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesMore
bwaVLTotalRxConcatenatedFramesMore.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of data fast frames concatenated with more then two frames received from the wireless media, including duplicate frames.

bwaVLDroppedFrameEvents.name: bwaVLDroppedFrameEvents
bwaVLDroppedFrameEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames that were dropped because they were retransmitted to the maximum allowed number of retransmissions without being acknowledged.

bwaVLFramesDelayedDueToSwRetry.name: bwaVLFramesDelayedDueToSwRetry
bwaVLFramesDelayedDueToSwRetry.description: Applicable to all units. Not applicable for units with SW Version 3.0 and higher. The number of frames that were delayed because the SW retry algorithm was activated on a previous frame designated for the same recipient.

bwaVLUnderrunEvents.name: bwaVLUnderrunEvents
bwaVLUnderrunEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames whose transmission was aborted because the rate of submitting frames for transmission exceeded the available transmission capability.

bwaVLOthersTxEvents.name: bwaVLOthersTxEvents
bwaVLOthersTxEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The number of Tx events due to problems other than those of the other Tx Events counters.

bwaVLTotalTxEvents.name: bwaVLTotalTxEvents
bwaVLTotalTxEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of Tx special events.

bwaVLPhyErrors.name: bwaVLPhyErrors
bwaVLPhyErrors.description: Applicable to all units, only when DFS is enabled. The number of unidentified signals.

bwaVLCRCErrors.name: bwaVLCRCErrors
bwaVLCRCErrors.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames received from the wireless media containing CRC errors.

bwaVLOverrunEvents.name: bwaVLOverrunEvents
bwaVLOverrunEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames that were discarded because the receive rate exceeded the processing capability or the capacity of the Ethernet port.

bwaVLRxDecryptEvents.name: bwaVLRxDecryptEvents
bwaVLRxDecryptEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The number of frames that were not received properly due to a problem in the data decryption mechanism.

bwaVLTotalRxEvents.name: bwaVLTotalRxEvents
bwaVLTotalRxEvents.description: Applicable to all units. The total number of Rx special events.

bwaVLAUAdbResetAllModulationLevelCounter.name: bwaVLAUAdbResetAllModulationLevelCounters
bwaVLAUAdbResetAllModulationLevelCounter.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. To reset all the counters for all SUs/RB in the MAC Address Database.

bwaVLAUAdbTable.name: bwaVLAUAdbTable
bwaVLAUAdbTable.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. AU/BU MAC Address Database table.

bwaVLAUAdbEntry.name: bwaVLAUAdbEntry
bwaVLAUAdbEntry.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. An entry in the AU/BU MAC Address Database table.

bwaVLAdbIndex.name: bwaVLAdbIndex
bwaVLAdbIndex.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The index of an entry in the AU/BU MAC Address Database table.

bwaVLAdbMacAddress.name: bwaVLAdbMacAddress
bwaVLAdbMacAddress.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The MAC Address of an SU/RB entry in the MAC Address Database table.

bwaVLAdbStatus.name: bwaVLAdbStatus
bwaVLAdbStatus.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The status of the relevant SU/RB.

bwaVLAdbSwVersion.name: bwaVLAdbSwVersion
bwaVLAdbSwVersion.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The SW version of the relevant SU/RB.

bwaVLAdbSNR.name: bwaVLAdbSNR
bwaVLAdbSNR.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The average Signal to Noise Ratio in dB of frames received by the AU/BU from the relevant SU/RB.

bwaVLAdbMaxModulationLevel.name: bwaVLAdbMaxModulationLevel
bwaVLAdbMaxModulationLevel.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The value configured in the relevant SU/RB for the Maximum Modulation Level parameter. Modulation Level 8 is not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLAdbTxFramesTotal.name: bwaVLAdbTxFramesTotal
bwaVLAdbTxFramesTotal.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link.

bwaVLAdbDroppedFramesTotal.name: bwaVLAdbDroppedFramesTotal
bwaVLAdbDroppedFramesTotal.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of frames intended to the SU/RB that were dropped because they were retransmitted to the extent of the maximum allowed number of retransmissions without being acknowledged.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel1.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel1
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel1.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 1.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel2.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel2
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel2.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 2.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel3.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel3
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel3.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/BU over the wireless link using modulation level 3.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel4.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel4
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel4.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 4.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel5.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel5
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel5.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 5.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel6.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel6
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel6.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/BU over the wireless link using modulation level 6.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel7.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel7
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel7.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 7.

bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel8.name: bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel8
bwaVLAdbTxSuccessModLevel8.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of unicast frames (excluding retransmissions) that were successfully transmitted to the SU/RB over the wireless link using modulation level 8. Not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel1.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel1
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel1.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 1.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel2.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel2
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel2.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 2.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel3.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel3
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel3.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 3.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel4.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel4
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel4.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 4.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel5.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel5
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel5.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 5.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel6.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel6
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel6.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 6.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel7.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel7
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel7.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 7.

bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel8.name: bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel8
bwaVLAdbTxFailedModLevel8.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Counts the total number of failures to successfully transmit unicast frames intended to the SU/RB using modulation level 8. Not applicable for units with HW revision A.

bwaVLAdbCirTx.name: bwaVLAdbCirTx
bwaVLAdbCirTx.description: Applicable to AU Only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. Read-only. The value configured in the relevant SU for the CIR: SU to AU parameter.

bwaVLAdbMirTx.name: bwaVLAdbMirTx
bwaVLAdbMirTx.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The value configured in the relevant SU/RB for the MIR: SU/RB to AU/BU parameter.

bwaVLAdbCirRx.name: bwaVLAdbCirRx
bwaVLAdbCirRx.description: Applicable to AU Only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The value configured in the relevant SU for the CIR: AU to SU parameter.

bwaVLAdbMirRx.name: bwaVLAdbMirRx
bwaVLAdbMirRx.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The value configured in the relevant SU/RB for the MIR: AU/BU to SU/RB parameter.

bwaVLAdbCirMaxDelay.name: bwaVLAdbCirMaxDelay
bwaVLAdbCirMaxDelay.description: Applicable to AU Only. Not applicable to BWA-PtP products. The value configured in the relevant SU for the CIR Maximum Delay parameter.

bwaVLAdbDistance.name: bwaVLAdbDistance
bwaVLAdbDistance.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The distance between the SU/RB and the AU/BU (In Kilometers).

bwaVLAdbHwRevision.name: bwaVLAdbHwRevision
bwaVLAdbHwRevision.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB HW Revision.

bwaVLAdbCpldVer.name: bwaVLAdbCpldVer
bwaVLAdbCpldVer.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB CPLD Version.

bwaVLAdbCountryCode.name: bwaVLAdbCountryCode
bwaVLAdbCountryCode.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB supported country code.

bwaVLAdbBootVer.name: bwaVLAdbBootVer
bwaVLAdbBootVer.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB Boot Version.

bwaVLAdbAtpcOption.name: bwaVLAdbAtpcOption
bwaVLAdbAtpcOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB ATPC option configuration.

bwaVLAdbAdapModOption.name: bwaVLAdbAdapModOption
bwaVLAdbAdapModOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB adaptive modulation option configuration.

bwaVLAdbBurstModeOption.name: bwaVLAdbBurstModeOption
bwaVLAdbBurstModeOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB burst mode option configuration.

bwaVLAdbConcatenationOption.name: bwaVLAdbConcatenationOption
bwaVLAdbConcatenationOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB concatenation option configuration.

bwaVLAdbSecurityMode.name: bwaVLAdbSecurityMode
bwaVLAdbSecurityMode.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB security mode configuration.

bwaVLAdbAuthOption.name: bwaVLAdbAuthOption
bwaVLAdbAuthOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB authentication algorithm configuration.

bwaVLAdbDataEncyptOption.name: bwaVLAdbDataEncyptOption
bwaVLAdbDataEncyptOption.description: Applicable to AU/BU Only. The SU/RB data encryption option configuration.

bwaVLAdbAge.name: bwaVLAdbAge
bwaVLAdbAge.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The time since any packet was received from the relevant SU/RB.

bwaVLAdbUnitName.name: bwaVLAdbUnitName
bwaVLAdbUnitName.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The unit name of the relevant SU/RB.

bwaVLMeasureUpLinkQualityIndicator.name: bwaVLMeasureUpLinkQualityIndicator
bwaVLMeasureUpLinkQualityIndicator.description: Applicable to SU/RB. Starts calculation of LQI. The calculation will be for a period of 10 seconds.

bwaVLReadUpLinkQualityIndicator.name: bwaVLReadUpLinkQualityIndicator
bwaVLReadUpLinkQualityIndicator.description: Applicable to SU/RB. The results of the last LQI calculation. Range: 1 to 8.

bwaVLUpLinkQualityIndicatorStatus.name: bwaVLUpLinkQualityIndicatorStatus
bwaVLUpLinkQualityIndicatorStatus.description: Applicable to SU/RB Only. Indicates the test conditions. fullTest means that there are no limitations on the range of available modulation levels, and that all modulation levels from 1 to 8 can be used. limitedTest indicates that the results may not indicate the true quality since the available range is limited - by HW (HW Revision A), or by the applicable parameters in the country code, or by the configurable Maximum Modulation Level parameter.

bwaVLMacPinpointTable.name: bwaVLMacPinpointTable
bwaVLMacPinpointTable.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. A table that contains information about wireless device used by a certain Ethernet station in order to connect to the wireless network

bwaVLMacPinpointEntry.name: bwaVLMacPinpointEntry
bwaVLMacPinpointEntry.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. An entry in the MAC Pinpoint Table. Each entry contains an Ethernet station MAC address and the MAC address of the wireless device used to connect it to the wireless network

mptEthernetStationMACAddress.name: mptEthernetStationMACAddress
mptEthernetStationMACAddress.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The MAC address of the Ethernet station. It is used as an index in the MAC Pinpoint Table.

mptUnitMACAddress.name: mptUnitMACAddress
mptUnitMACAddress.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. The MAC address of the wireless device used by the station with the MAC Address from the index in order to access the wireless network.

bwaVLDrapGatewaysTable.name: bwaVLDrapGatewaysTable
bwaVLDrapGatewaysTable.description: This table provides information about Gateways supporting DRAP that are registered at the AU

bwaVLDrapGatewayIP.name: bwaVLDrapGatewayIP
bwaVLDrapGatewayIP.description: The IP address of the Gateway

bwaVLDrapGatewayNoOfActiveVoiceCalls.name: bwaVLDrapGatewayNoOfActiveVoiceCalls
bwaVLDrapGatewayNoOfActiveVoiceCalls.description: The current number of active voice calls handled by the Gateway

bwaVLTrapSUMacAddr.name: bwaVLTrapSUMacAddr
bwaVLTrapSUMacAddr.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. SU/RB MAC Address.

bwaVLTrapToggle.name: bwaVLTrapToggle
bwaVLTrapToggle.description: Applicable to all units. An On/Off toggle status.

bwaVLTrapParameterChanged.name: bwaVLTrapParameterChanged
bwaVLTrapParameterChanged.description: Applicable to all units. A modification to one of the parameters related to CIR/MIR, IP Filtering or VLAN.

bwaVLTrapAccessRights.name: bwaVLTrapAccessRights
bwaVLTrapAccessRights.description: Applicable to all units. The access rights used for login.

bwaVLTrapLog.name: bwaVLTrapLog
bwaVLTrapLog.description: Applicable to all units. Login or logout to the Monitor program via Telnet.

bwaVLTrapTelnetUserIpAddress.name: bwaVLTrapTelnetUserIpAddress
bwaVLTrapTelnetUserIpAddress.description: Applicable to all units. The IP address of a Telnet user.

bwaVLTrapRTx.name: bwaVLTrapRTx
bwaVLTrapRTx.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. Retransmissions as a percentage of total transmissions.

bwaVLTrapFtpOrTftpStatus.name: bwaVLTrapFtpOrTftpStatus
bwaVLTrapFtpOrTftpStatus.description: Applicable to all units. The status of the last FTP/TFTP loading procedure.

bwaVLDFSMoveFreq.name: bwaVLDFSMoveFreq
bwaVLDFSMoveFreq.description: Applicable to AU/BU with HW revision B and lower (for units with HW revision C and higher replaced by bwaVLTrapDFSMoveFreq New to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz). The new frequency in MHz after detecting radar on a previous channel.

bwaVLDFSMoveFreqNew.name: bwaVLDFSMoveFreqNew
bwaVLDFSMoveFreqNew.description: Applicable to AU/BU. The new frequency in MHz after detecting radar on a previous channel. (Replaces bwaVLDFSMoveFreq to support a resolution of 0.5 MHz for units with HW revision C and higher).

bwaVLEthBroadcastThresholdExceeded.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastThresholdExceeded
bwaVLEthBroadcastThresholdExceeded.description: Applicable to all units. The number of packets that are dropped by the ethernet broadcast/multicast limiter.

bwaVLTrapSubscriberType.name: bwaVLTrapSubscriberType
bwaVLTrapSubscriberType.description: Applicable to AUS only. The type of subscriber that was rejected by AUS

bwaVLTrapMACAddress.name: bwaVLTrapMACAddress
bwaVLTrapMACAddress.description: Applicable to BU/RB only. The MAC address of the BWA PtP unit whose type has been changed

bwaVLNewUnitTypeTrap.name: bwaVLNewUnitTypeTrap
bwaVLNewUnitTypeTrap.description: Applicable to BU/RB only. The new type of the BWA PtP unit.

bwaVLTrapSWVersion.name: bwaVLTrapSWVersion
bwaVLTrapSWVersion.description: The SW version of the SU that tries to associate with a station that has Wireless Link Prioritization Enabled

bwaVLSUassociatedAUTRAP.name: bwaVLSUassociatedAUTRAP
bwaVLSUassociatedAUTRAP.description: An AU/BU trap indicating a new association with an SU/RB.

bwaVLAUdisassociatedTRAP.name: bwaVLAUdisassociatedTRAP
bwaVLAUdisassociatedTRAP.description: An AU/BU trap indicating that an SU/RB has been disassociated from the AU. The AU/BU decides that an SU/RB has been disassociated from it and remove it from the ADB after receiving from another AU/BU a SNAP frame with the SU/RB MAC address. The SNAP frame indicating a network topology change where the SU/RB has associated with another AU/BU will be received if both AUs/BUs are connected to the same Ethernet backbone.

bwaVLAUagingTRAP.name: bwaVLAUagingTRAP
bwaVLAUagingTRAP.description: An AU/BU trap indicating that the unit association was aged out and removed from the Association database following its failure to acknowledge a specified number of consecutive frames.

bwaVLSUassociatedTRAP.name: bwaVLSUassociatedTRAP
bwaVLSUassociatedTRAP.description: An SU/RB trap indicating association with an AU/BU. In addition to the MAC address information of the AU/BU, the trap also includes information on the average SNR of frames received from the AU/BU.

bwaVLAUwirelessQualityTRAP.name: bwaVLAUwirelessQualityTRAP
bwaVLAUwirelessQualityTRAP.description: An AU/BU trap, indicating that the quality of the wireless link (retransmissions rate) has changed and dropped below (Off) or increased above (On) a threshold , defined by the *bwaVLWirelessTrapThreshold. The threshold for AU/BU is a percentage of retransmissions.

bwaVLPowerUpFromReset.name: bwaVLPowerUpFromReset
bwaVLPowerUpFromReset.description: An AU/BU trap indicating power up after Reset.

bwaVLTelnetStatusTRAP.name: bwaVLTelnetStatusTRAP
bwaVLTelnetStatusTRAP.description: Applicable to all units. A trap indicating that a log-in or log-out has been performed via Telnet. Includes the log-in access right and the IP address of the PC performing Telnet.

bwaVLParameterChangedTRAP.name: bwaVLParameterChangedTRAP
bwaVLParameterChangedTRAP.description: Applicable to all units. A trap indicating a change in a CIR/MIR, IP Filter or VLAN parameter.

bwaVLLoadingStatusTRAP.name: bwaVLLoadingStatusTRAP
bwaVLLoadingStatusTRAP.description: Applicable to all units. A trap indicating that last FTP/TFTP loading process has been finished successfully or failed.

bwaVLPromiscuousModeTRAP.name: bwaVLPromiscuousModeTRAP
bwaVLPromiscuousModeTRAP.description: An AU/BU trap, indicating that the AU/BU In (On) Promiscuous Mode or out (Off) Promiscuous Mode.

bwaVLDFSRadarDetecetedTRAP.name: bwaVLDFSRadarDetecetedTRAP
bwaVLDFSRadarDetecetedTRAP.description: DFS: Applicable to AU/BU only. A trap indicating that a radar was detected.

bwaVLDFSFrequcnyTRAP.name: bwaVLDFSFrequcnyTRAP
bwaVLDFSFrequcnyTRAP.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. A trap indicating that the unit moved to a new frequency.

bwaVLDFSNoFreeChannelsExistsTRAP.name: bwaVLDFSNoFreeChannelsExistsTRAP
bwaVLDFSNoFreeChannelsExistsTRAP.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. A trap indicating that a radar was detected and there is no free channel.

bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticatLimiterTRAP.name: bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticatLimiterTRAP
bwaVLEthBroadcastMulticatLimiterTRAP.description: Applicable to all units. The trap is send if the ethernet broadcast filter threshold is exceeded and it contains the number of dropped packets.

bwaVLAUSUnsupportedSubscriberTypeTRAP.name: bwaVLAUSUnsupportedSubscriberTypeTRAP
bwaVLAUSUnsupportedSubscriberTypeTRAP.description: Applicable to AUS only. This trap is generated when a subscriber with unsupported type tries to associate to AUS. The AUS supports only SU-3 and SU-6. The first variable of the trap is the subscriber MAC Address. The second variable is the type of subscriber

bwaVLUnitTypeChangedTRAP.name: bwaVLUnitTypeChangedTRAP
bwaVLUnitTypeChangedTRAP.description: Applicable to BU/RB only. This trap is generated when the user change the type of the BWA PtP unit. The RB can be converted in BU or vice versa. The first variable of the trap is the unit MAC Address. The second variable is the new type of the unit

bwaVLWLPrioritizationNotSupportedBySUTRA.name: bwaVLWLPrioritizationNotSupportedBySUTRAP
bwaVLWLPrioritizationNotSupportedBySUTRA.description: Applicable to AU/BU only. This trap is generated when an SU/RB with a SW version below 4.0 that does not support Wireless Link Prioritization is associated with an AU/BU with thw Wireless Link Prioritization Option enabled. The first variable of the trap is the SU/RB MAC Address. The second variable is the SW version of the SU/RB
